INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(146,1,'Blend together all the ingredients in a blender till smooth.  Adjust sweetener to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(146,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(146,3,'Cook mixture on the stove top. Bring to a boil on low heat, stiring constantly till thickened.  When thickened, pour mixture into individual serving dishes & chill till firm.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(146,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(146,5,'"Vegetarian Times" March, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(147,1,' Place onion in a large pot with 1/2 cup water.  Cook and stir until onion softens slightly, about 3 minutes. Add remaining 5 cups of water, potatoes, zucchini, and soy saue.  Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 35 minutes.  Add spinach and pepper. Cook for another 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Puree soup in batches in blender. Return to pan. Add mushrooms if desired.  Heat gently for 5 minutes. Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(147,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(147,3,' Author''s Note:  Pureed potatoes give this soup a rich taste and texture with barely a trace of fat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(147,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(147,5,' Source: Vegetarian Times, May 1993 Low Fat, Fabulous and Fit by Mary McDougall Formatted MM:de');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(147,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(147,7,'A.ENGLISH [Al & Diane]       at 21:49 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,1,'Combine scallions, cucumber, tomatoes,  parsley, oil, cider vinegar, tabasco with the cayenne & allspice to make the salsa.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,3,'Saute onions & garlic in remaining oil for 2 to 3 minutes.  Add celery & carrots & cook for another 2 minutes.  Add pepper & continue to saute till the vegetables are tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,5,'Whisk together the tomato paste with 1/4 cup of red wine, cider vinegar, sugar, mustard, herbs & spices.  Add to the vegetables.  Combine the beans with the vegetables & stir thoroughly,  Simmer for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,7,'Layer the saute mixture with the hot rice & salsa & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(148,9,'"New Recipes From Moosewood Restaurant"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,1,'Rinse and sort the peas, then place in a large bowl and add enough cold water to cover.  Stir in baking soda.  Let soak overnight.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,3,'Drain peas, rinse several times in cold water and drain thoroughly.  Let stand at least 30 minutes, then spread out on paper towels and let dry thoroughly.  In a deep, heavy saucepan, heat about 2 inches of oil to 350 F (180 C) or until a 1-inch bread cube turns golden brown in about 65 seconds.  Add peas, a portion at a time, and cook until golden.  (Be careful when cooking peas; even when completely dry, they often cause oil to bubble to top of pan.)  Remove peas from hot oil with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,5,'Turn cooked peas into a small bowl.  Sprinkle with chili powder, coriander, cinnamon, cloves and salt; mix to coat peas with spice mixture. Cool completely; store in an airtight container until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,7,'Makes about 1-3/4 cups.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(149,9,'Source: The Book of Appetizers by June Budgen (HP Books/Price Stern Sloan) Typographical errors courtesy of: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(150,1,'Combine the sauce ingredients together in a small bowl and set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(150,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(150,3,'Heat the 1 1/4 cups oil in a deep-fat fryer or a large wok until it almost smokes.  Deep-fry the bean curd cubes in two batches.  When each batch of bean curd cubes is lightly browned, remove and drain well on paper towel.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(150,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(150,5,'Arrange the bean curd cubes on a platter and serve the peanut sauce separately as a dipping sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(150,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(150,7,'Ken Hom, "Asian Vegetaraian Feast"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(151,1,'(Couscous-Chickpea Croquettes) ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~ If using sunflower seeds, preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spread seeds on a baking tray. Remove any shells or discolored seeds. Bake to 5-7 min., until seeds smell nutty and darken slightly. Grind seeds in a food processor for 30 seconds until coarsely chopped. Add chickpeas and process until well mixed. Keep mixture in the food processor. In a heavy, 1 qt. pot, combine couscous, tomato juice and red wine. Stir and bring to a boil. Lower heat, cover and simmer for 2-3 min., until couscous has absorbed all the liquid. Let sit 5 more minutes. Add cooked couscous to chickpea mixture along with remaining ingr. except oil. Mix well, stopping the processor and scraping down the sides once or twice, until smooth. Lightly oil your hands. Shape 2 to 3 . Tbl. of chickpea mixture between your hands to form a ball. Repeat with remaining mixture until you have 24 balls. Flatten balls to form patties about 2" wide and 1/2" thick. Brush croquettes with olive oil and place on a lightly oiled baking tray. Bake for 15 min, turn the croquettes over, bruth with oil and bake another 10-12 min. Makes 24 2" croquettes. These may be served in a sandwich, as an appetizer or as a main dish with pasta and tomato sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(151,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(151,3,'From: the January 1993 issue of Vegetarian Times');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(151,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(151,5,'FROM:    JANICE MESSALI   (SWSH14B)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(152,1,'In a medium sized bowl, warmed, dissolve yeast in water & add salt, oil & sugar.  Stir together.  With a slotted spoon, beat in 1 3/4 c flour. Combine 1/2 c flour with the other ingredients.  Set side in a warm area for 15 to 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(152,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(152,3,'Flour a board with the rest of the flour & turn out the dough.  Knead till it is no longer sticky.  Flatten it with the palms of your hands.  Fold in half & in half again.  Roll until it is 10 1/2 inches long.  Sprinkle cornmeal on a cookie sheet & set the dough.  Use a brush to oil the surface.  Slash the top of the dough with a sharp knife & allow to proof for 30 minutes or so.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(152,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(152,5,'Preheat oven to 375F & bake for 20 minutes.  Remove from oven & spread the surface with water, using a brush.  Continue to bake for 30 to 35 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(152,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(152,7,'Anne Lerner, "Breads You Wouldn''t Believe"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(153,1,'Dissolve the yeast in the water in a bowl.  Add salt, oil & garlic.  Stir in 3 c flour & wheatgerm. Mix with a fork.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(153,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(153,3,'Sprinkle 1/4 c flour on a board & turn out the dough, coating it with the flour.  Then knead, adding another 1/4 c flour gradually.  Knead for a couple of minutes.  Let rise till it has doubled in size.  Punch down & let it rest for a while.  Roll the dough into a 13 inch length.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(153,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(153,5,'Set the bread on an oiled sheet.  Let proof for 20 minutes.  Preheat oven to 375F & bake for 45 to 55 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(153,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(153,7,'Anne Lerner, "Breads You Wouldn''t Believe"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(154,1,'In a deep bowl, measure our the rye flour.  Make a well in the centre. Dissolve the yeast in the water & add to the bowl.  Add salt, oil & vinegar.  Stir vigorously.  Add the white flour.  Knead well till the dough is pliable.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(154,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(154,3,'Form into a round bread.  Use a brush to oil the surface & set in a 9" round pan.  Allow to double in size.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(154,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(154,5,'Preheat oven to 350F & bake for 1 hour 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(154,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(154,7,'Anne Lerner, "Breads You Wouldn''t Believe"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(155,1,'Combine all ingredients except water & glaze in a food processor & process for 30 seconds.  Gradually add water while the machine is running. Process in short bursts till a thick ball is formed.  Remove & knead for 5 minutes.  Use flour as needed to prevent sticking.  Cover dough with a damp cloth & let rise in a warm dark place for 15 to 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(155,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(155,3,'Prepare grill & cover to buld up an intense heat.  Cut dough into 6 portions.  roll each piece into a circle 8" in diameter & as thin as a flour tortilla.  Brush each piece with glaze & place glaze side down on the grill.  Cover & allow to bake for 5 minutes.  Brush tops with glaze, flip & allow other side to brown.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(155,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(155,5,'PER SERVING: 227 Cal.; 5g Prot.; 5g Fat; 41g Carb.; 0 Chol.; 17mg Sod.; 3g Fiber.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(155,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(155,7,'"Vegetarian Times" July, 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(156,1,'Heat oven to 350F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(156,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(156,3,'Mix together the mango chutney, turmeric & curry powder.  Mix in the almonds, ensuring that they become well coated.  Spread them on a non-stick baking sheet.  Bake for 10 minutes.  Spread them no plates to cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(156,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(156,5,'Store almonds in covered containers & add them to salads or serve with drinks.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(156,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(156,7,'Gail Duff, "A Book of Herbs & Spices"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(157,1,'Combine chilies, ginger, cumin seeds & mustrad seeds in a small bowl. Heat ghee in a large pot.  When hot, add the spices.  When the mustard seeds start to pop, drop in the potatoes & cauliflower.  Fry for 4 minutes or so.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(157,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(157,3,'Add the tomatoes, turmeric, coriander, garam masala, sugar, salt & half the minced coriander.  Mix well, cover & gently heat for 15 minutes.  If the vegetables start to stick, add a few drops of water.  Top with remaining coriander & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(157,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(157,5,'Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,1,'Saute onion in olive oil till golden.  Add carrots, garlic, spices & lemon juice.  Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.  Add water, cover pan tightly & simmer until the carrots are tender, about 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,3,'Puree in a blender.  Add small amounts of soy milk or water if necessary.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,5,'In a pot, melt ghee & add flour.  Cook for 2 minutes, stirring often.  Add the rest of the soy milk & sweetener.  Cook stirring until the sauce is very hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,7,'Combine sauce with puree.  Heat for 10 minutes & then serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(158,9,'Joel Rapp, "Mother Earth''s Vegetarian Feasts"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(159,1,'In a large pot, heat oil.  Fry onion & garlic for a couple of minutes. Add potatoes, carrots & bell pepper & continue to fry for a few more minutes, stirring occasionally.  Add spices & stir fry for a couple of seconds.  Add lentils & tomato paste , stir quickly & add water.  Cover, raise heat & bring to a boil.  Reduce heat & simmer gently for 30 minutes. Add salt & pepper.  Check the water levels & lentil consistency.  Cook for another 15 minutes if lentils are not cooked.  Remove from heat & let cool slightly.  The mixture should be moist but not swimming in water.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(159,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(159,3,'Roll out the pastry & line a 9" pie plate.  Add the filling & cover with remaining pastry.  Bake at 400F/200C for 30 to 40 minutes until the pastry is browned.  Serve with chutney, chili sauce & a salad.  Good cold.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(159,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(159,5,'Very loosely drawn from "Entertaining with Cranks"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(160,1,'Wash lentils.  Cook till tender but firm.  Heat olive oil in large pot & when hot add garlic.  Saute for 1 minute.  Add spinach leaves & steam till they wilt.  Add lentils & rest of ingredients.  Cover & simmer for 15 minutes.  Serve over rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(160,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(160,3,'Nava Atlas, "Vegetariana"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(161,1,'Combine ginger, green chilies & coconut in blender with 1/3 cup of water till smooth.  Add garam masala & pulse for a few seconds. Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(161,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(161,3,'Heat ghee.  Whe hot, add mustard & cumin seeds & fry for a few seconds. Stir in the asafetida & almost immediately put in the potatoes.  Stir fry for 5 minutes Then pour in the mixture from the blender.  Add the turmeric, coriander, eggplant, salt & half the fresh coriander.  Mix very gently so as not to break the vegetables.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(161,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(161,5,'Reduce heat & fry very gently until the liquid has evaporated.  Mix in lemon juice & remaining coriander greens & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(161,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(161,7,'Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(162,1,'Put all ingredients in a small pot & simmer.  Stir constantly.  Cook for 5 or 6 minutes or till mixture thickens.  Remove from heat, cover & let sit for a while.  Store left overs in fridge.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(162,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(162,3,'Makes 2 cups.  Serve on mashed potatoes, biscuits, pasta or vegetables.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(162,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(162,5,'"Vegetarian Times" October, 1991.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(163,1,'Heat oil & saute garlic for 1 minute.  Add carrot, barley, bay leaf & 2 1/2 c stock.  Bring to a boil, cover & simmer for 15 minutes.  Puree half the chick peas & add to the pot with the spinach, zucchini & seasonings. Simmer covered for another 10 minutes.  Add the rest of the chick peas, the remaining stock & lemon juice.  Simmer gently for another 15 minutes until the barley is tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(163,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(163,3,'Adapted from Nava Atlas, "Vegetariana"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(164,1,'Rinse the chick peas & soak them.  Drain well.  Add the chick peas to the water with the bay leaf & a small amount of ghee.  Bring to a boil & simmer for 1 hour.  Drain & reserve the liquid.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(164,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(164,3,'Using a mortar & pestle, grind the cinnamon stick, peppercorns, cardamom, cloves & cumin seeds.  Heat 3 tb ghee in a skillet.  When hot, stir in the ginger root, chilies & fry till browned.  Remove from heat & sprinkle in the turmeric, paprika, coriander, cayenne & asafetida.  Return to heat & add diced tomato.  Stir fry for 4 to 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(164,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(164,5,'Stir in salt, chick peas, 1/2 cup of reserved cooking water & lemon juice. Simmer till the liquid has appreciably thickened.  Sprinkle with the crushed spices & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(164,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(164,7,'Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,1,' 1.  Heat green onions and olive oil or water in a medium skillet and sautee for 3 minutes. Add flour and stir well to dissolve. Add nutritional yeast and slowly add water, whisking to combine ingredients into a smooth sauce. Stir in tahini and vegetable broth.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,3,' 2.  Whisking continuously, allow sauce to cook over medium heat until it begins to bubble. Whisk in soymilk. Cook sauce for 2 minutes, whisking continuously until it is thick and bubbly. Season with freshly ground black pepper and ground rock salt, if desired.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,5,' Yields 1 1/2 to 2 cups of sauce, enough for one pound of pasta.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,7,' Variation: Stir 2 cups of cooked corn into finished sauce and pour over 1 pound of thin green pasta.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(165,9,' From _American Vegetarian Cookbook_ by Marilyn Diamond');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(166,1,'Combine dates, water & oil or shortening.  Let cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(166,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(166,3,'Combine the baking soda with the flour & mix well.  Add the brown sugar, baking powder, vanilla, salt & nuts to the date mixture.  Mix well.  Gently fold in the flour & baking soda mixture.  If too dry, add a little more water.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(166,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(166,5,'Bake in greased muffin pans at 325F for 25 minutes, or until cooked through.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(166,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(166,7,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(167,1,'Cut tofu into 1" squares.  Mix together sesame seeds, cornstarch & flour. Roll tofu in sesame mixture till well coated.  Heat oil in skillet till hot. Fry squares till well browned.  Drain on paper towels & set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(167,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(167,3,'Place the rest of the ingredients in a pot.  Add just enough water to cover by 1/2".  Bring to a boil then simmer for 20 minutes.  Blend till smooth.  Pour into a serving bowl.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(167,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(167,5,'To serve, place toothpicks in tofu cubes.  Arrange on a platter & serve warm with the sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(167,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(167,7,'Jack Santa Maria, "Chinese Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(168,1,'1) Roll the tofu cubes in the wheat germ mixed with cornstarch. Heat the oil to 350F on a deep-fat frying thermometer. 2) Fry the cubes, a few at a time, in a basket in the hot oil. Drain on paper towels and keep warm while making the remainder. 3) Serve with soy sauce or sweet and sour sauce dip. From The New York Times New Natural Foods Cookbook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(169,1,'In a mortar pound the drained moong beans to form a paste.  Add the other ingredients in turn, stirring well.  Pluck a small piece of the paste and form into a ball the size of a walnut.  Do not mould too tightly. Deep-fry the balls until golden brown, drain and serve with the thick sweet sauce below.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(169,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(169,3,'THE SAUCE: Gently heat the three ingredients until the sugar dissolves. Allow to cool before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(169,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(169,5,'Source: Thai Vegetarian Cooking by Vatcharin Bhumichitr Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(170,1,'Cut the bean curd into 1- x 1-1/2-inch flat pieces.  Deep-fry them in hot oil for 2 to 2-1/2 minutes, until the surfaces are somewhat firm and yellow.  Drain thoroughly.  Soak the mushrooms in boiling water for half an hour.  Drain.  Discard the stems and cut the caps into halves.  Cut the onion into thin slices.  Break the broccoli into individual florets and cut the stem into 1-inch wedges.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(170,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(170,3,'Heat the vegetable oil in a large frying pan or wok.  When hot, add the onion, ginger, broccoli stems, and mushrooms and stir-fry in the hot oil for 2 mintues, to season the oil.  Add the broccoli and stock and continue to stir-fry for 1-1/2 minutes, and then cook, covered, for 1-1/2 minutes. Uncover the pan or wok, pour the sauce ingredients over the contents, and continue to turn and stir-fry all ingredients together for a further 1-1/2 minutes.  Serve with rice and other dishes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(170,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(170,5,'Source: New Chinese Vegetarian Cooking by Kenneth Lo Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(171,1,'Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.  Add the liquid in order, stirring well after each addition.  Mix until smooth.  Bake at 350F for 35 minutes in a square pan.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(171,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(171,3,'Source Unknown');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,1,'Wash legumes & soak for an hour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,3,'Place water & legumes in a large pot & bring to a boil.  Cut vegetables into bite sized pieces & add to the legumes.   Cook for 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,5,'Heat ghee in a separate pot & saute onion & garlic till golden.  Stir in chili, turmeric & garam masala.  Mix thouroughly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,7,'Transfer legumes & vegetables into pot with ghee mixture & stir well.  Add salt & cook for another 20 minutes until everything is tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,9,'Add lemon juice & cilantro & serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(172,11,'Michael Pandya, "Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(173,1,'Combine all ingredients in a bowl.  Will keep indefinitely if stored in the refrigerator.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(173,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(173,3,'"Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(174,1,'This stuffing is for eggplants, pepper, tomatoes and zucchini. It is made with olive oil and served as a cold vegetable dish.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(174,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(174,3,'Slice onion very finely, skin and roughly chop tomato and wash the rice until the water runs clear. Heat the olive oil in a deep pot and fry the onion until it becomes soft. Add the tomato, pine nuts, currants, sugar, thyme and season and then stir in the drained rice and fry them together for two or three minutes. Cover with just enough water to come half an inch above the the level of the rice and then boil out the water and steam for a few minutes until the rice mixture is dry. Allow to cool. Stuff veggies with mixture, arrange in a flat roasting pan, cover each one with its lid (after insides are scooped out and sprinkled w/ salt). Pour around them enough water to come half-way up their sides. Bake in a 350 oven for 45 min. or until they are well cooked through & soft, but have not lost their shape. Sprinkle w/ chopped dill and parsley. Enough stuffing for 2 pounds of peppers.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(174,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(174,5,'Recipe from "Home Book of Turkish Cookery" by Venice Lamb.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(174,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(174,7,'Posted by DEBORAH AKYUREK, Prodigy ID# DNJS60B.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,1,'Sautee the onion with half the oil. Add the rice and let cook for a few minutes. Add the dill, the hot water and salt and pepper. Boil for about 5 minutes. Let it cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,3,'Steam the grape leaves and rinse with plenty of water in a collander.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,5,'Wrap the rice mixture with the grape leaves. This is the most difficult and time consuming part, although after you are through it a couple of times you enjoy it the most. It is better if two people work on it simultaneously, talking, joking etc. You want to make them small in size (about 1-2 inches.) Do not hesitate to cut big leaves in half. Discard the central stem of these leaves and if you can reduce (with a sharp knife) any other tough stems it would be good. You want to wrap the rice very tightly. You place the rice in one end, fold from the short end and the two sides and then roll while pushing the rice downwards to pack it really tight. You have to do it a couple of times to understand. If they are not tightly packed they will unroll later. Also be careful to wrap totally, do not leave any holes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,7,'You arrange the dolmadakia in a casserole, tightly. Make more than one layers. Add the lemon juice, the rest of the olive oil and 1 1/2 cups of hot water. Cover them with a plate or something to keep them in place. Let them simmer for 35 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,9,'Serve then cold, with strained yogurt or taramosalata. Enjoy.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,11,'Georgios');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(175,13,'Posted by: rika@informix.com (Rika Tsitsinia)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(176,1,'Heat the 1/2 cup oil in a skillet.  Add the onion and scallions and saute for about 5 minutes, until soft and transparent.  Add the garlic and cook for a few minutes, then add the rice, dill, parsley, lemon juice, salt, pepper, and remaining 1/4 cup olive oil.  Stir well, then add the hot water.  Cover and simmer about 5 minutes.  Remove from the heat and cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(176,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(176,3,'Meanwhile, carefully remove the grapevine leaves from the jar, leaving the brine in the jar.  Wash grapevine leaves thoroughly and drain, then with a sharp knife cut the heavy stems from the leaves.  (If using fresh grapevine leaves use the same procedure, parboiling leaves for 5 minutes when not tender, then drain.)  Line an enameled pan with a few heavy grapevine leaves and set aside.  To stuff a grapevine leaf, put it on your working surface rough side up and stem end near you, and place a teaspoonful of the rice mixture near the stem end.  Using both hands, fold the part of the leaf near you up and over the filling.  Then fold the right side of the leaf over the filling, then the left side, and roll tightly and back away from you and toward the pointed end of leaf.  Place the "dolma", seam side down, in the prepared pan.   Continue stuffing grapevine leaves until the mixture has been used.  (If any grapevine leaves remain, replace in the reserved brine for future use.)  Place an inverted plate on the dolmades, then add enough water to cover the dolmades (about 1 to 1-1/2 cups).  Bring to a boil, then cover the pan, lower the heat, and simmer as slowly as possible for 1-1/4 hours, then taste one to see if the rice is tender, and continue cooking slowly if necessary.  Cool, then chill.  Serve cold, as an appetizer or as an entree.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(176,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(176,5,'Note:  An important variation, particularly in Macedonia and Thrace: add a few tablespoons of raisins and pine nuts to the filling when adding the rice.  Also, you may vary the size of dolmades as you wish by adding 1-1/2 teaspoons of the filling.  However, be consistent to allow them to cook at the same rate.  They may be stored in the refrigerator for a week or so.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(176,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(176,7,'Source: "The Food of Greece" by Vilma Liacouras Chantiles.  Avenel Books, New York. Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(177,1,'Put the tomatoes in a saucepan Add 1.8l of water Add the celery, onion, carrot, oil, salt and pepper. Simmer for 30 minutes then add the spaghetti Serve when the spaghetti is cooked (about 10-15 minutes)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(177,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(177,3,'Posted by Kaz Dunkley');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(178,1,'Place the garlic, pepper, olive oil, lemon juice, and salt in a food processor or blender and puree until the garlic is finely chopped (if preparing by hand, finely dice and mash the garlic, then mix with the other ingredients).  Add the chick-peas and continue mixing to a smooth paste. Garnish with the chopped parsley.  Maybe served at room temperature or chilled. Makes about 4 1/2 cups of dip SUGGESTED DIPPERS: Pita Bread Or Toast Triangles, Scallions, Bland Water Crackers, Red Cabbage');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(178,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(178,3,'Posted by Sandee Eveland in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(179,1,'This is a favourite hangover dish - the chilis kick-start the benumbed body while the lime leaf refreshes and clears the jaded palate.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(179,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(179,3,'In a wok or frying pan/skillet, heat the oil until a light haze appears. Add the garlic and chilis and fry until the garlic is golden brown.  Add the noodles, stir, add the remaining ingredients and stir well until the peppers begin to cook but are still al dente.  Turn on to a dish.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(179,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(179,5,'Source: Thai Vegetarian Cooking by Vatcharin Bhumichitr Typos by: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(180,1,'Sift dry ingredients into a bowl.  Add liquid.  Mix well.  Transfer to 13 X 9 X 2-inch pan.  Bake at 350F for 35 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(180,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(180,3,'Source Unknown');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(181,1,'Heat oil in large soup pot.  When hot, saute onion for 5 minutes, take care not to let it brown.  Add potatoes and fry for, covered for 3 minutes.  Add oregano, basil, parsley, salt & pepper.  Cook covered for 2 minutes.  Add tomatoes and cook for another 5 minutes.  Add the stock, bring to a boil, reduce heat & simmer for 20 minutes, or until the potatoes are tender.  Check seasonings.  Let cool, blend till smooth. Reheat before serving, but take care not to let it boil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(181,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(181,3,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,1,'Directions: Place soy milk in food processor (or blender).  Put on lowest setting.  Drizzle oil into soy milk.  Add other ingredients. I add about the same amount of lemon juice in addition to the vinegar. Someatimes I add one tablespoon of dry mustard.  You''ve got to try adding basil and/or sage and/or oregeno.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,3,'I''ve also never had a problem adding all the vinegar, syrup, salt, etc. to the soy milk first and then adding the oil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,5,'You cannot fail.  Try it.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,7,'I got the basic recipe from Shirley Wilkes-Johnson.  She is a gourmet cook and inventor.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(182,9,'JORGE [Jorge]                at 21:02 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,1,'Cut unpeeled eggplants into 1/2" diagonal slices, spread slices onto a cutting board, sprinkle with salt & press with a plate to get rid of excess liquid.  Allow to drain for 30 minutes.  Wipe with a damp cloth.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,3,'Heat enough olive oil to cover bottom of a large skillet.  Fry gently over medium heat, turning often till tender.  Remove from pan & drain.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,5,'Plunge tomatoes into boiling water for a few seconds, peel & deseed. Saute remaining pulp in a little olive oil till soft.  Add garlic & parsley.  Cover, reduce heat & cook for 30 to 40 minutes.  Remove from heat, cool, add lemon juice, sugar, salt & pepper.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,7,'Place eggplant in a shallow serving dish or glass bowl.  Pour tomato mixture on top & chill till ready to serve.  Garnish with parsley sprigs.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(183,9,'"Vegetarian Times Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(184,1,'Rub the ghee over the cut side of the eggplant.  Roast until the skin is lightly burned.  The eggplant should be completely soft & tender.  Peel & mash the pulp with a potato masher.  Mix well with onion, chilis, salt, cilantro & oil.  Fry in a skillet with a little oil for 3 to 5 minutes. The mixture should be fairly dry.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(184,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(184,3,'Chakravarti & Morizot, "Not Everything we Eat is Curry"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,1,'Wash, peel and slice eggplant into 1/4" pieces. Spread slices out on racks or paper towels, then sprinkle with lemon juice and salt. Let stand 5-10 min then wipe off with paper towels. While eggplant is standing, mix flour, cornmeal, oregano, garlic powder and black pepper together in a bowl. Preheat oven to 350. Dredge eggplant slices in flour-cornmeal mix. Lay on cookie sheet spread with the oil. Oven-fry slices for 8-10 min on each side or until golden brown.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,3,'Ricotta-Style Filling: While the eggplant slices are baking, prepare the tofu filling. Process the tofu, lemon juice, basil, honey, salt and garlic in food processor to a fine grainy texture like ricotta cheese.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,5,'Cover bottom of 8x8" pan with 1/3 of the tomato sauce. Use half the oven fried eggplant slices to cover the bottom of the pan. Then spread the tofu filling over, reserving 1/2 cup for the top. Next, cover the tofu filling with the rest of the eggplant slices, and pour the remaining tomato sauce over the top. Arrange reserved tofu mix in small dollops over the top. Bake about 45 min or until dollops are slightly browned.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,7,'Makes 4 to 6 servings. per serving: Cal 318, Protein 17 g, Fat 12 g, Carbs 36 g.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(185,9,'FROM:    MADELINE HIMY   (NFBH49A)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,1,'Cook rice, sauteing it in olive oil & crumbling in the saffron before adding the water & salt.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,3,'Brush a large baking pan with olive oil.  Leaving the stems on, slice the eggplants in half lengthwise & place face down on the pan.  Add sherry & water.  Cover tightly with aluminum & bake at 375F till tender, about 45 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,5,'Meanwhile, saute the onions in 2 tb olive oil for 10 minutes.  Add peppers, 1 tb sherry & cayenne.  Saute covered for 5 minutes.  Stir in tomatoes, currants, parsley & black pepper.  Simmer covered for a few minutes.  Combine rice & vegetable mixture.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,7,'When eggplants are cool enough to handle, gently mash them & push the soft middle to the side.  Mound the rice pilaf on each eggplant half.  Pour tomato juice into baking pan, cover tightly & return to oven to bake about 30 minutes.  Serve garnished with almonds & parsley.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(186,9,'"New Recipes From Moosewood Restaurant"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(187,1,'In a pot, cover eggplant with cold water, bring to a boil & cook for 1/2 an hour.  Drain & press with a spoon to remove excess moisture.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(187,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(187,3,'Combine eggplant & tomatoes with remaining ingredients.  Saute in moderately hot olive oil for 5 minutes.  Stir & mash ingredients together as sauteing.  Chill before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(187,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(187,5,'"The Africa News Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(188,1,'Cut the eggplants in half lengthwise.  With a small knife, cut away the eggplant flesh from the skin without breaking the skin (if planning to stuff the shells, leave 1/4-inch of the flesh with the skin as a firm base) and set the shells aside.  Dice the eggplant flesh and push through the medium blade of a meat grinder as quickly as possible to avoid discoloration.  (Or the eggplant may be pureed in a blender or food processor.)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(188,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(188,3,'Heat the oil in a frying pan and saute the scallions and garlic.  Add the parsley, fennel, allspice, wine, and the diluted tomato paste.  Stir in the eggplant pulp, season with salt and pepper, and simmer for 20 minutes. Taste to adjust seasonings.  Add the bread crumbs to absorb excess liquid.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(188,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(188,5,'Stuff the eggplant shells, if desired, and place in an oiled baking dish. Bake in a moderate oven (350 F) for 35 minutes.  Serve warm - or particularly good - cold.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(188,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(188,7,'From: "The Food of Greece" by Vilma Liacouras Chantiles.  Avenel Books, New York. Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,1,'Preparation time: 20 minutes Baking Time: 1 hour');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,3,'In a large pot, bring water to boil. Slice the eggplant in half and scoop out the insides. Place the eggplant shells in the water and cook until soft, about 10 minutes. Chop the eggplant insides and set aside to saute.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,5,'In another saucepan, bring the quinoa and water to a boil, then reduce the heat, cover, and cook until all the water is absorbed, about 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,7,'In a large frying pan, add the water and heat over medium heat. Then add the onion, garlic, peppers, and the eggplant insides, and saute, adding a little more water as needed. Then add the tomato puree, salt, pepper, walnuts, and chickpeas. Cover and simmer about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,9,'Preheat oven to 350.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,11,'Turn off the heat for all three pans. Drain the eggplant shells from the water. Add the cooked quinoa, wheat flour, and gluten flour to the vegetable saute and stir well. Place the eggplant shells in a large casserole dish with a cover. Fill the eggplant shells with the quinoa mixture. Put the cover on the casserole dish, and place in the oven. Bake at 350 for 1 hour. Serve with a steamed vegetable, such as cauliflower, and a green salad, such as a spinach salad.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(189,13,'~Mary Howard From: howard@iscsvax.uni.edu @Newsgroups: rec.food.veg');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,1,'Heat oil in a frying pan over medium heat.  Add garlic, onions & saute for 5 minutes.  Season with 1 tb tamari & half the garlic, basil & salt.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,3,'In a small pot, combine the flour & nutritional yeast.  Add water, tahini & the rest of the seasonings.  Mix well.  Over a low heat, cook slowly for 15 minutes, stirring frequently until the sauce thickens.  If too thick, add more liquid.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,5,'Oil an 8 X 12 inch baking dish.  Pour in a layer of sauce, then a layer of sliced eggplant & a layer of onions.  repeat the layering, finishing with the sauce.  Sprinkle with Paprika.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,7,'Bake at 350F for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(190,9,'"The Cookbook for People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,1,'Sprinkle eggplant with salt, place in a colander & set aside for 20 to 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,3,'In a medium pot, heat ghee.  Saute onion till translucent.  Add all the spices in order & saute for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,5,'Rinse eggplant.  Add to the pot along with the apple juice & water. Cover & simmer over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,7,'In another pot, cook the spinach in a very small amount of water till it becomes limp but remains bright green.  Drain & cool.  Chop when cool enough to handle.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,9,'Add bell pepper to the eggplant, cook for 5 minutes.  Stir in spinach, lemon juice & extra salt if required.  Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,11,'Serve over rice toped with toasted cashew nuts.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(191,13,'"Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(192,1,'Heat the oil with half of the mustard seeds in a large saucepan.  Add remaining mustard seeds when the cooked seeds begin to pop.  Add the garlic and saute until tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(192,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(192,3,'Add the spinach, a small amount at a time, stirring occasionally to keep the spinach from scorching.  When the spinach wilts, add the eggplant, ginger, jalapeno chiles, tumeric, paprika, coriander, and cumin.  Saute to blend the flavors.  Cover, and cook over medium-low heat for 15 minutes. Add the tomatoes and season to taste with salt.  Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.  Garnish with cilantro.');
