INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(275,7,'Anne Lerner, "Breads You Wouldn''t Believe"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(276,1,'Boil the potatoes in their jackets until just fork tender.  Peel them & mash them until they are very smooth.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(276,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(276,3,'Add the remaining ingredients except the ghee.  Knead until well blended. Divide into 8 portions.  Wash & dry your hands & then rub them a little vegetable oil.  Roll each ball in your hands & then flatten into a small round patty about 1/2 inch thick.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(276,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(276,5,'Brush a griddle or skilet with ghee.  Place over the lowest heat possible &, when the pan is hot, add the patties in a single layer.  Pan fry for 15 to 20 minutes per side until a redish brown crust is formed.  Serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(276,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(276,7,'Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,1,'Wash the potatoes & cut them evenly into julienne strips.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,3,'Combine the ginger root, chilies, coconut, parsley in a bowl.  Add a little water or soy milk, mix well.  Drop in potato strips.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,5,'Heat the ghee in a heavy pot, drop in the whole cloves, cinnamon, bay leaf. Fry till the cumin seeds turn brown.  Add the marinated potatoes & stir fry till they are lightly browned.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,7,'Add the rice, salt, turmeric, lemon juice, water & sugar.  Stir & quickly bring to a full boil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,9,'Reduce heat to very low & cover with a tight fitting lid.  Simmer gently for 20 to 25 minutes.  5 minutes before the end, add the peas.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,11,'Remove lid, turn off heat & add 1 tb ghee.  Let rice sit for 5 minutes. Fluff & garnish each portion with lemon wedges.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(277,13,'Adapted from Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(278,1,'A.)   Rinse the hijiki in a fine-mesh strainer under cold running water. In 3 times the amount of warm water, soak for 10 to 15 minutes.  Remove the hijiki with a tea strainer.  (Sand and pebbles will sink to the bottom of the bowl.)  Return to fine-mesh strainer and drain off excess water. Grate the carrots into matchstick slivers.  Dip the age puff for 30 seconds in boiling water, and cut into matchstick slivers.  Place tofu in a heated skillet and mash with a spatula.  Let it simmer in its own water until reduced to small crumbs.  Snap the ends off the green beans and place in boiling water for 1 to 2 minutes.  Immerse in iced water, drain, and cut into 1/2-inch-long pieces.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(278,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(278,3,'B.)   In a heated skillet, saute sesame oil, hijiki, carrots, age, and tofu (all completely drained of water).  When ingredients have acquired a shiny appearance, add dashijiru, shoyu, sake and mirin.  Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring frequently, until liquid has been absorbed.  Turn off heat and add green beans.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(278,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(278,5,'C.)   Place B in serving dish, sprinkle with sauteed sesame seeds.  If you like, add seven-taste pepper to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(278,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(278,7,'Source: The Folk Art of Japanese Country Cooking, by Gaku Homma Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,1,'Preheat oven to 375 F.  Remove loose, papery skin from garlic and cut in half crosswise.  Rub cut surfaces with olive oil.  Wrap garlic in foil and bake 35 to 40 minutes until garlic is soft.  Set aside until cool enough to handle.  Squeeze garlic cloves from their skins.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,3,'Remove stems and seeds from chilies.  Roast chilies under broiler, turning frequently, until skin is evenly blistered and slightly charred.  Place chilies in a paper bag and let cool.  Remove skins from chilies and rinse.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,5,'Toast pumpkin seeds in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat, shaking the pan often, until seeds have puffed, about 3 minutes.  Do not brown.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,7,'Transfer seeds to a small bowl, then set aside to cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,9,'Grind pumpkin seeds to a fine meal in a food processor or blender.  Add roasted garlic, chilies, tomatillos, peppers and cilantro and continue pureeing until smooth.  Heat sauce in a medium skillet and add stock. Simmer 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,11,'Slice tofu 1/2-inch thick.  Brush tofu with tarmari and grill over hot coals or broil in oven, 5 minutes per side.  Serve tofu on a bed of rice topped with mole sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,13,'Calories per serving: 497 Grams of fat: 17 Percent fat calories: 32 Cholesterol: 0 mg Grams fiber: 8.4');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(279,15,'Source: Delicious! magazine - May/June 1993 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(280,1,'Put the tomatoes in a saucepan with 500ml of cold water. Simmer for 30 minutes and add the vegetables, oil and seasoning Cook for 45 - 60 minutes until the vegetables are tender. Serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(280,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(280,3,'Posted by Kaz Dunkley');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(281,1,'Line a serving dish with lettuce and set aside.  Fry the garlic in the oil until golden brown and set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(281,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(281,3,'In a saucepan, heat the stock and add the fresh mushrooms, cook momentarily, then add all the other yam ingredients and stir for approximately one minute until thoroughly mixed.  Finally, add the garlic oil and mix, turn on to the lettuce and garnish with coriander.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(281,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(281,5,'Source: Thai Vegetarian Cooking, by Vatcharin Bhumichitr Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(282,1,'In a large pan, bring the vegetable stock to the boil and stir in the Nam Prik Pow sauce.  Add the remaining ingredients and simmer, stirring well until the mushrooms are just cooked but still al dente.  Pour into a serving bowl and garnish with coriander leaves.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(282,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(282,3,'Source: Thai Vegetarian Cooking by Vatcharin Bhumichitr Typos by: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(283,1,'Combine yeast with water in a mixing bowl.  Combine the rest of the ingredients except the currants & flour.  Mix well.  Add 1 1/2 c flour & mix.  Stir in currants.  Mix in the remaining 2 c of flour.  Remove from bowl & knead, adding more flour as necessary.  Knead for a few minutes until the dough is pliable.  Return to mixing bowl, cover with a damp cloth & set aside until it has doubled.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(283,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(283,3,'Punch dough down, turn out onto a floured board, cover & let rest for 10 minutes.  Divide the dough into 18 pieces.  Roll into a ball & place on a greased baking sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.  Flatten slightly.  If you wish, using a sharp knife, cut out a cross in the top of each bun.  Cover with a damp cloth & let rise till doubled.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(283,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(283,5,'Heat oven to 375F.  Lightly brush the top of each bun with vegetable oil & bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.  Cool on wire racks.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(283,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(283,7,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,1,'In a large skillet, add white grape juice and heat over medium-high heat. Stir fry carrots, onion, and celery for two minutes. Remove from heat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,3,'In a small bowl, stir together water, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, and bouillon cube, crumbling cube as much as possible.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,5,'Add mixture to skillet.  Cook and stir over medium-high heat 1 to 2 minutes, or until mixture is thickened and bubbly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,7,'Stir in black and kidney beans.  Cook additional 2-3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until mixture is heated through. Garnish with sliced red onions, if desired.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,9,'May be served hot or cold.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(284,11,'One serving of 2/3 C = 2 bread exchanges; 164 cal; 33 gm carb; 6 gm protein; trace fat, 304 mg sodium, 0 mg cholesterol. (Sodium may be reduced by cooking dry beans instead of using canned, using no added salt)');
