INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(285,1,'Blanch green beans for 2 minutes.  In a small bowl, combine garlic, scallions, chilies, beans.  In another small bowl, combine vinegar, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar & wine.  Heat oil in a wok, add bean mixture & stir-fry for a minute.  Add green beans & stir-fry for 5 minutes.  Mix in the rest of the ingredients & stir-fry long enough just to coat the beans.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(285,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(285,3,'"Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(286,1,'Combine all ingredients in a pot.  Over a medium heat, simmer till slightly thickened, should take 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(286,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(286,3,'Vegetarian Times" July, 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(287,1,'Heat oil in a wok & fry the onion, garlic & chili for 30 seconds.  Add salted beans & bean curd, fry gently till bean curd turns golden.  Add the rest of the ingredients & cook until the sauce thickens.  Serve hot over noodles or fried rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(287,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(287,3,'Jack Santa Maria, "Chinese Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(288,1,'Combine chickpeas with their juice with baking soda & bring to a boil. Immediately remove from heat, drain & rinse thoroughly.  In a food processor, combine chickpeas, tahini, garlic, lemon juice, salt & 1 Tb of water.  Blend till creamy.  Add rest of the water if mixture apears too thick.  Refrigerate.  Heat olive oil & fry pine nuts till golden brown. When ready to serve, sprinkle over hummus.  Serve cold with pita bread.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(288,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(288,3,'"The Hamilton Spectator", July 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(289,1,'Drain & rinse chick peas.  Put them in a large pot with lots of fresh water & boil for 60 minutes.  If the chick peas are old, then you may have to boil them for longer.  Cook until they are soft.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(289,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(289,3,'Drain thoroughly, reserving the liquid.  Grind to a fine powder.  Add 150 ml of reserved stock & blend to a stiff paste.  You may have to add more stock.  Add all the other ingredients & mix thoroughly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(289,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(289,5,'Leave to stand at least 2 hours so that the flavours can marry.  Add more seasonings if you require, especially lemon juice & olive oil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(289,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(289,7,'Adapted from Sarah Brown''s "Vegetarian Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,1,'In a medium saucepan place the soaked chickpeas and cover them with water. Bring the water to a boil over high heat and vigorously cook the chickpeas for 10 minutes.  Reduce the heat to low and simmer the chickpeas for 1« hours, or until they are tender (add more water if necessary).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,3,'Drain the water from the chickpeas.  Place them in a food processor (reserve 8 chickpeas for the garnish) and pure them until they are very smooth.  Add some water if necessary.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,5,'In a medium bowl, place the pured chickpeas.  Add the garlic, salt, pepper, tahini, and lemon juice.  Mix the ingredients together so that they are well blended.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,7,'Add the corn oil and mix it in well so that a smooth paste is formed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,9,'In a small serving bowl, place the humus.  Smooth it down evenly with a knife.  Pour the olive oil in the center.  Sprinkle on the paprika and parsley.  Garnish the dish with the reserved chickpeas.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,11,'Makes 1¬ cups.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(290,13,'Source: Papa Garo''s - Redondo Beach, California "Southern California Beach Recipe" by Joan and Carl Stromquist ISBN: 0-9622807-3-9 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(291,1,'* (I like sourdough, and I recommend not using a really dark type.)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(291,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(291,3,'Put everything but the bread and margarine into the blender/food processor/ other implement of destruction and blend until the herbs are medium chooped. Pour the resulting batter into a wide shallow dish.  (She says it''ll keep three days covered in the frig, if you plan meals that far ahead.  I don''t.)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(291,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(291,5,'Melt the margarine in a big skillet or frying pan.  Soak one slice of bread at a time in the batter until pretty gloppy, then toss into the skillet and fry until the bottom is medium brown, then flip and cook about another minute.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(291,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(291,7,'Serve right off the stove.');
