INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(294,3,'"Vegetarian Times"  July, 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(295,1,'Heat a wok & coat with oil.  Add onion & carrot & saute for 3 minutes till onion is slightly browned.  Add crumbled tofu & the remaining ingredients. Stirring constantly, saute over medium low heat for a bout 5 minutes, or until the tofu is light & dry.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(295,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(295,3,'Variations:  Add 1/4 c of any of the following: parboiled green peas; shiitake mushrooms; diced bamboo shoots.  Also try adding 1 ts grated ginger.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(295,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(295,5,'Shurtleff & Aoyagi, "The Book of Tofu"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(296,1,'Boil or bake the potatoes, then pass through a foodmill.  Mix the flour, salt, oil & herbs with the potatoes.  On a floured board, roll this dough to a thickness of about 1/4 inch.  Cut into triangles 3 or 4 inches wide. Fry in very hot oil on both sides until light golden.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(296,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(296,3,'Vera Gewanter, "A Passion for Vegetables"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(297,1,'Combine flours, wheatgerm, baking powder & soda & salt.  Stir in oats & sugar.  Mix thoroughly.  Add raisins.  Combine oil, molasses & water.  Add to dry ingredients.  Stir until thoroughly blended.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(297,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(297,3,'Turn into greased 23 X 13 X 7 cm loaf pan.  Bake at 350F for 50 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(297,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(297,5,'Adapted from the Ontario Ministry of Health Recipes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,1,'Cut eggplant, squash & zucchini into pieces 1/4" thick.  Halve mushrooms & cut bell peppers into strips.  Quarter removing skins only if they are dirty.  Trim outer leaves of fennel & remove any dirt.  Slice into 8 thin wedges.  Place all vegetables into large bowl.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,3,'MARINADE: Strip thyme leaves from stems, reserve stems.  In a processor, process thyme, red pepper, zest & salt & pepper.  Add garlic while machine is running.  Stop machine & add lemon juice  Turn on & add vegetable broth in a slow stream.  Process 1 minute.  Pour over vegetables & allow to marinate for 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,5,'Preapre grill & cover to build intense heat.  Skewer vegetables.  Toss sthyme stems onto the heat shield or coals.  Place brochettes onto hot grill, cover & allw to smoke for 5 minutes.  Remove cover, turn & cook for another 3 to 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,7,'Meanwhile, drain marinade into a small non-reactive pot.  Add tomato sauce & heat through.  When skewers are almost done, cook pasta.  Drain & return to pot.  Pour sauce over pasta & toss to coat.  Serve with grilled vegetables.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,9,'VARIATION: Use sourdough bread brushed with the marinade & lightly grilled instead of the pasta.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,11,'PER SERVING: 314 Cal.; 14g Prot.; 3g Fat; 58g Carb.; 0 Chol.; 240mg Sod.; 8g Fiber.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(298,13,'"Vegetarian Times" July, 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(299,1,'Preheat oven to 400F.  Place whole eggplant, unpeeled, on a rack in oven. Wrap the two peppers & celery stalks individually in aluminum foil & place them on rack as well.  Bake for 30 minutes.  Remove peppers & celery & let cool.  Bake eggplant for another 15 minutes.  It should be very tender & have collapsed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(299,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(299,3,'When vegetables are cool enough to handle, peel eggplant, cut into several pieces & drain in a colnder for 20 minutes.  Squeeze out some of the excess moisture.  Chop peppers, removing stems & seeds.  Leave in large pieces.  Chop celery into 1/2" pieces.  Dice eggplant & combnie with peppers & celery in a large bowl.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(299,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(299,5,'Heat a few drops of olive oil in a skillet & saute the garlic till golden. Add to hte bowl.  Add remaining ingredients & mix thoroughly.  Cover & let stand for 1 hour at room temperature before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(299,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(299,7,'Nava Atlas, "Vegetariana"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,1,'Heat olive oil in a Dutch oven.  Add onion, bell pepper, herbs & salt. Saute over medium heat until the onion is fairly soft, 8 to 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,3,'Add tomatoes, tomato paste, honey & black pepper.  Bring to a boil.  Lower heat & simmer, partially covered, for 20 to 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,5,'Add garlic & cook 10 minutes more.  Either let the sauce sit for a couple of hours or serve now.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,7,'Serve over spaghetti & with homemade garlic bread.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(300,9,'Mollie Katzen, "Moosewood Cookbook", Revised Edition');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,1,'  1 c  dried red kidney beans, washed');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,2,'       coconut milk (see NOTE)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,3,'  1 ea sprigfresh thyme');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,4,'  1 ea clove garlic, crushed');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,5,'  1 ea green onion, chopped');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,6,'       salt, to taste');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,7,'  3 sl hot pepper, such as Scotch Bonnet (optional) 2 1/4 c uncooked long-grain, regular or parboiled rice In a medium saucepan with a tight-fitting lid, place the washed beans. Add the coconut milk and bring to boil.  Reduce the heat. Cook until the beans are tender, 1 to 2 hours.  Add the thyme, garlic, green onion, and salt. Add the hot pepper if desired. Simmer for a few minutes. Add the rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,9,'The liquid should come up to 1-inch above the rice.  Add water if needed. Cover the pot.  Bring to a boil again.  Reduce the heat to low. Cook for 15 minutes (for regular rice) to 20 minutes (for parboiled). It should not be necessary to add more water, but if to much liquid boils away, replace it with boiling water.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,11,'The rice is ready when the liquid disappears and the grains of rice are separate.  Stir just before serving to evenly distribute the red kidney beans. Makes 4 to 6 servings.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,13,'NOTE:  For coconut milk, crack 1 mature coconut with a hammer, cut off');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,14,'     the brown shell, and grate the coconut meat.  Into a bowl, add');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,15,'     the coconut meat and 6 cups of water.  Mix well, then squeeze to');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,16,'     extract as much liquid as possible.  Press through a sieve and');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,17,'     use as directed above.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,18,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,19,'     Etoria says his preferred method to separate the coconut');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,20,'     meat from the brown shell is with a butter knife ("or the');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,21,'     dullest knife you have") to prevent cuts.  Slip the knife');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,22,'     between the white flesh and the shell, and it should come');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,23,'     away easily.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,24,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,25,'    Stanley Etoria, chef of the Reggae Cafe, 6100 Westheimer,');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(301,26,'    Houston, Texas');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,1,'Leaving stems on, cut eggplants in half lengthwise.  Mix together the sherry, soy sauce & molasses.  Oil a baking pan.  Pour sherry mixture into pan, place eggplant slices face down, cover tightly & bake at 350F for 45 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,3,'Brown cubed tempeh, 1/2c of onions, 1 ts fennel & cayenne in oil for 20 minutes.  Stir frequently to avoid burning.  In a separate pot, saute remaining onion, coriander, remaining fennel till onions are transluscent. Add peppers & mushrooms & saute 15 to 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,5,'With a slotted spoon, lift tempeh & onions from oil & stir into sauted vegetables.  Stir in tomato paste & 2 tb braising liquid from eggplant pan.  Salt filling.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,7,'Turn eggplant halves over, carefully mash pulp & push to sides leaving a hollow centre.  Fill each hollow with 1/4 of filling.  Cover pan tightly & bake at 350F for 20 minutes til piping hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,9,'Serve on bed of rice, pour over some juiice from baking pan & sprinkle with scallions & sesame seeds.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(302,11,'"New Recipes From Moosewood"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(303,1,'HEAT WATER IN LARGE PAN. Meanwhile, with sharp knife, remove stems of ruffled kale leaves. Chop stems into 1-inch long pieces and add them to the water. Cut leaves into pieces about 2-inch square, wash well and set aside. Scrub and peel potatoes and add peels to heating water along with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 bay leaf. When water boils, lower heat and let it simmer while you assemble remaining ingredients. Cut peeled potatoes into pieces about 1/2-inch square. Heat oil in soup pot, add onion, garlic, red pepper flakes and remaining bay leaf. Cook over medium-high heat 3 or 4 minutes, stirring frequently, then season with salt. Stir in potatoes and 1 cup strained simmering stock. Cover and cook slowly 5 minutes. Add kale, cover again and steam until leaves are wilted, stirring once or twice. Strain remaining stock into soup pot. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer slowly, covered, until potatoes are soft, about 30 minutes. Use back of wooden spoon to break up potatoes by pressing them against sides of pot or puree 1 or 2 cups soup in blender and return it to pot to make unifying background for other elements. Taste soup and season to taste with salt and generous grinding of pepper. If possible, set soup aside 1 hour to allow flavors to merge and develop even further, then serve with light sprinkling of parsley.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(303,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(303,3,'Deborah Madison, "Prodigy Guest Chefs Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,1,'Wash the gram beans.  Place both the grma beans & kidney beans in a large pot.  Add 4 cups of water & bring to a boil.  Turn off heat & let sit for 2 hours.  Add the onions, ginger, tomatoes, 1 cup water, cardamom, coriander, pepper, salt & 6 tb ghee.  Mix well, bring to a boil & simmer for 4 1/2 to 5 hours.  Keep the heat very low so that you maintain a bare simmer during the cooking period.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,3,'After cooking, remove 2 to 3 cups of the beans & blend them till smooth. Return to the pot.  Keep the dal on a low simmer.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,5,'Heat ghee & add the cumin seeds when ghee is very hot.  After 10 seconds, add the minced onion & cook gently for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over the dal & mix in the coriander.  Simmer till heated through.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,7,'Serve with Royal Vegetable & Rice Casserole.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(304,9,'Julie Sahni, "Classic Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(305,1,'In a large pot, bring water to a boil & add kasha: cook for 15 to 20 minutes, till soft.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(305,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(305,3,'Heat oil in a skillet & add the chopped vegetables.  Saute for 7 minutes till soft.   Mix kasha & add to the vegetables.  Add seasonings, using more if necesary.  Add tahini & cook for 8 to 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(305,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(305,5,'"The Cookbook for People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,1,'White grape juice is just as good as white wine if you want to avoid the alcohol. The recipe works well without either.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,3,'I made this one up when I couldn''t be bothered to follow a recipe, so I''d be interested to know what you think of it. It is also nice with a crumble topping - I use an ordinary wholemeal crumble mix and add sunflower seeds to it, or cashew nuts, to give it a slightly nutty taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,5,'Preparation: chop the onions into 2cm pieces and finely dice the');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,6,'            mushrooms.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,7,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,8,'Add all the vegetables to a casserole dish, then add the spices, chickpeas, yoghurt and white wine. If possible leave to marinate for a couple of hours to let the vegetables absorb the taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,9,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,10,'Microwave on high (650w oven) for 15 minutes, or longer if you want the vegetables to be soft rather than crunchy - say 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,11,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,12,'Serve with Biryani rice - I use brown rice with lentils, almonds, sultanas and a mixture of vegetables such as carrots and broccoli.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,13,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(306,14,'Posted by Kaz Glover in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(307,1,'Combine TVP & water in a bowl.  Let syand for 10 minutes.  Heat oil in a large cast-iron skillet or wok.  Stir-fry onion, garlic & ginger for 5 minutes.  Add TVP & stir-fry another 5 minutes.  Add tomato paste, tomatoes, curry powder, salt & cayenne.  Simmer a few minutes.  Add peas & mushrooms.  Bring to a boil, cover & simmer over low heat for 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(307,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(307,3,'"Vegetarian Times" February, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(308,1,'In a stewpot, saute onion, garlic, chilies in the oil for 5 minutes.  Add cinnamon, cloves, potatoes & cook for another 5 minutes, covered.  Stir in tomatoes, green beans & cover & cook for 5 minutes more.  Add the zucchini & corn.  Simmer, covered on low heat till the vegetables are tender.  If the stew seems too dry, add some tomato juice or water.  Add cilantro & salt to taste.  Serve with cornbread.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(308,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(308,3,'"Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(309,1,'Heat oil in a large pot over medium heat & fry the onions for 20 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent burning.  Add garlic & cook for 2 minutes. Add turmeric & pepper.  Stir rapidly for a moment, then add the tomatoes & ginger.  Cook for about 5 minutes (the fat should be separating from the gravy).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(309,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(309,3,'Add tamarind & about 1 cup of the chick pea stock.  Cover & simmer gently for 15 minutes.  Add chick peas, garam masala & cumin.  Cook for 10 minutes.  Check for salt.  Serve garnished with onion slices & shredded green chilies.  Serve with Poori.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(309,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(309,5,'Julie Sahni, "Classic Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,1,'Steep peas in boiling water for 1 hour.  Drain & rinse well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,3,'In a large pot, heat oil & fry onions & spices for 4 minutes over a medium heat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,5,'Add split peas, rice & green chili.  Mix well.  Pour on water & lemon juice.  Add tomatoes, stir once & cover.  Simmer very gently for 40 minutes or until rice is soft.  Season & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,7,'Sarah Brown''s "Vegetarian Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(310,9,'Split peas can be substituted for lentils.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,1,'Scrub and cook potatoes in boiling, salted water until tender.  Peel and mash.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,3,'Place burghul in a fine sieve and rinse with cold water.  Press with back of spoon to extract moisture, then turn into a large bowl and leave for 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,5,'Add potatoes, grated onion, parsley, mint, cinnamon, salt and plenty of pepper.  Mix, taste and add more salt if necessary.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,7,'Knead well with hand, moistening it occasionally with water.  If mixture is too soft add enough flour to make a firm paste, kneading well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,9,'Put sliced onion and half the oil in a 25 x 30 cm (10 x 12 inch) baking dish or 30 cm (12 inch) round dish.  Dot potato paste over onions, then spread evenly with a spatula.  Cut into diamond shapes using an oiled knife.  Pour remaining oil evenly on top and bake in a hot oven for 40 minutes or until golden brown.  Cool in dish, then serve at room temperature with salad.  Good served hot, in which case cool for 10 minutes before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(311,11,'Source: The Complete Middle East Cookbook - by Tess Mallos ISBN: 1 86302 069 1 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(312,1,'Soak cabbage in salted water to cover 5 to 10 hours. Drain. Combine cabbage with salt, green onions, garlic, chile and gingerroot. Mix well and spoon into large jar. Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 days before using. Keeps well several weeks. Use as relish or salad.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(312,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(312,3,'Makes about 1 quart');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(312,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(312,5,'(C) 1992 The Los Angeles Times');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(312,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(312,7,'Posted by Karen Mintzias in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,1,'Makes: 30 Oven temperature: 200 C (400 F) reducing to 180 C (350 F) Cooking time: 30 minutes');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,3,'Peel pumpkin, remove seeds and cut into 5 mm (1/4 inch) dice.  Measure and place diced pumpkin into a bowl.  Add remaining filling ingredients, stir to combine, cover and leave for 12 hours or overnight.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,5,'Sift flour and salt into a mixing bowl, add oil and rub in with fingertips until distributed evenly.  Add water and lemon juice and mix to a firm dough.  Knead lightly, cover and leave to rest for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,7,'Roll out dough thinly (about the thickness of a normal pie crust) and cut into 15 cm (6 inch) rounds.  Take a round of pastry and moisten edges with a little water.  Place a good tablespoonful of filling in centre, fold over and press edges to seal well.  Flute edge with fingers or press with tines of fork.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,9,'Place finished pies on lightly greased baking trays and glaze tops with an egg beaten with a little milk.  Bake in a hot oven for 10 minutes, reduce to moderate and bake for further 20 minutes.  Serve hot or cold.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,11,'                 From: "The Complete Middle East Cookbook" by Tess Mallos');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,12,'                 ISBN: 1 86302 069 1');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(313,13,'                 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,1,'Soak the dried mushrooms in warm water for 20 minutes until soft.  Squeeze the excess liquid from the mushrooms and remove and discard the stalks. Cut the caps into shreds.  Soak the cloud ears in warm water for about 20 minutes or until soft.  Rince them well in cold water and drain them thoroughly in a colander.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,3,'Soak the noodles in a large bowl of very hot water for 15 minutes.  When soft, drain well.  Cut the noodles into 3-inch lengths, using scissors or a knife.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,5,'Peel and finely shred the carrot.  Finely shred the pepper and onion.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,7,'Heat a wok or large frying pan and add the oil.  When moderately hot, add the mushrooms, cloud ears, carrot, onion, green pepper, and water and stir-fry for 5 minutes or until the carrots are cooked.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,9,'Combine the sauce ingredients and add them to the vegetables. Give the mixture a good stir, then add the noodles.  Stir-fry the mixture for 2 minutes until well heated through. Serve at once or at room temperature.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(314,11,'Source: Asian Vegetarian Feast - by Ken Hom William Morrow and Company, Inc. - New York ISBN: 0-688-07753-6 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(315,1,'Mix all ingredients.  Serve with sauteed bean curd.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(315,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(315,3,'Madhur Jaffrey''s "World of the East Vegetarian Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,1,'This is classed as an ''oil'' dish by Coptic Egyptians and is prepared during periods of fasting when animal products cannot be taken.  You may cook the lentils, macaroni and rice simultaneously in 3 pots, or if, like me, you like to keep pots to a minimum, use the method given.  This is the way they prepare it in Egypt anyway.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,3,'Place lentils in a sieve and wash well under running water.  Place in a large pot and add 3 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt.  Bring to the boil, then simmer for 1 hour until tender but still intact.  Drain and keep aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,5,'Clean same pot and add 4 cups water.  Bring to the boil, add 2 teaspoons salt and the macaroni.  Stir constantly until water returns to the boil and cook, uncovered, for 15 minutes until tender.  Stir occasionally. Drain and keep aside.  Clean pot again and dry.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,7,'Wash rice well in sieve under running water and drain.  Heat oil in pot and fry rice over medium heat for 2-3 minutes.  Add 2 cups water and 1 teaspoon salt and bring to the boil, stirring occasionally.  Cover and simmer over low heat for 15 minutes or until tender.  Leave covered off the heat for 5 minutes for grains to separate.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,9,'Prepare the ta''leya (directions below), add tomato puree and bring to the boil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,11,'Add lentils and macaroni to cooked rice and toss together lightly with a fork.  Pour hot ta''leya and tomato mixture on top, toss again and cover pot.  Leave over low heat for 10 minutes.  Serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,13,'TA''LEYA: Halve peeled onions lengthwise then slice thinly to give semicircles.  Heat olive oil in a pan, add onions and fry over medium heat until golden brown.  Add garlic and cook a minute longer.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(316,15,'Source: The Complete Middle East Cookbook, by Tess Mallos Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(317,1,'Wash lentils thoroughly.  Place in a saucepan with the turmeric & 5 cups of water.  Bring to a boil, stirring often.  Reduce heat & simmer, partially covered, for 25 minutes.  Stir occasionally.  Add lemon juice to lentils & cook for a further 15 minutes.  Turn off heat & beat with a wire whisk.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(317,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(317,3,'Heat ghee, when very hot, add cumin seeds & fry for about 10 seconds. Remove pan from the heat & add red pepper & minced garlic.  Stir rapidly for 10 seconds until the garlic begins to colour, but do not let it brown. Pour over the hot puree.  Serve immediately.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(317,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(317,5,'Julie Sahni, "Classic Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(318,1,'Cook eggplant in boiling water (salted) 8-10 min., drain well. Saute onion, garlic, mushrooms in olive oil. Add flour, stir until smooth. Add tomatoes and other ingredients.  Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Layer in lightly grease 1 qt. casserole.  Bake at 375 degree for 25 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(318,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(318,3,'Source Unknown');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,1,'Bake the pita bread so that it is dry.  Break the bread up into small pieces and set them aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,3,'In a medium bowl place the lettuce, red bell peppers, cilantro, scallions, tomatoes, parsley, mint, and sumac.  Toss the ingredients together.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,5,'Add the olive oil and toss it in well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,7,'Add the lemon juice, cinnamon, salt and pepper.  Toss the ingredients together well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,9,'Add the pita bread pieces and toss them in.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(319,11,'Source: Papa Garo''s - Redondo Beach, California "Southern California Beach Recipe" by Joan and Carl Stromquist ISBN: 0-9622807-3-9 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(320,1,'RINSE THE CRACKED WHEAT several times then cover with water by 1/2-inch and let soak for 20 minutes, then drain well, squeezing out excess water. Combine minced onion with the allspice, pepper and salt. Set aside. In a large bowl, combine the parsley, scallions, tomatoes and mint. Gently fold in the drained wheat and refrigerate until an hour before serving. Just before serving, stir in the seasoned onion and dress with lemon juice and oil to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(320,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(320,3,'Deborah Madison, "Prodigy Guest Chefs Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(321,1,'Split & thoroughly wash leeks.  Cut into chunks.  Dice potaotes & chop the tomatoes.  Thinly slice onions.  Melt 3 tb ghee in pot & add onions & leek.  Simmer very gently for 5 minutes.  Add tomatoes followed by potatoes.  Simmer gently for 2 minutes.  Add stock.  Bring to a boil. Stir in sugar, salt & pepper to taste.  Reduce heat & simmer. Cook until potatoes are soft.  Cool & then blend, using extra water if necessary.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(321,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(321,3,'Re-heat before serving.  Top with croutons.  Thin with water if desired. Will keep well in the fridge.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(321,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(321,5,'Nava Atlas, "Vegetariana"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(322,1,'TRIM THE ARTICHOKES. Break off the tough outer leaves and slice off the top 2/3 of the remaining inner leaves. Trim the outsides, cut the artichokes in quarters and remove the chokes. Dice the trimmed hearts into small pieces. Put them in the acidulated water as you work. Keep the garlic cloves whole. Warm the olive oil and add the leeks, drained artichokes, garlic, potato, lettuce or sorrel, parsley and mint. Season with the salt, add 1/2 cup water and stew gently until the vegetables are wilted, about 5 minutes. Add the peas and the rest of the water. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer, partially covered, for 20 minutes or until the artichokes are cooked. Taste for salt. Puree the soup or leave it as is and serve with the freshly ground pepper, add a few good pinches of chervil or parsley, a spoonful of olive oil drizzled into each soup plate and a dusting of cheese.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(322,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(322,3,'Deborah Madison, "Prodigy Guest Chefs Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(323,1,'Wash pigeon peas & boil them with the water & turmeric & salt for 20 minutes.  Heat oil in medium pot, add mustard & cumin seeds & fry until mustard seeds start to pop.  Stir in onion & garlic & fry till browned & & soft.  Mix in ground chili & stir for 30 seconds.  Remove & pour over peas.  Stir thoroughly, cover & simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.  Serve hot with plain rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(323,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(323,3,'Rani, "Feast of India"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(324,1,'Place all ingredients in a blender and blend until the mixture is smooth. Cool and use as desired.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(324,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(324,3,'Source: Friendly Foods - by Brother Ron Pickarski, O.F.M.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(324,4,'       ISBN: 0-89815-377-8');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(324,5,'       Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(325,1,'Beat shortening for 30 seconds.  Add sugar & continue to beat till light & fluffy.  Combine lemon juice & water.  Combine the dry ingredients. Alternately mix the dry & wet ingredients with the beaten mixture.  Mix well.  Drop by spoonful onto a greased cookie sheet.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(325,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(325,3,'Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 450F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(325,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(325,5,'Makes about 60 to 70.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(325,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(325,7,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(326,1,'In a mortar, pound together the chilis, galangal and shallots to form a paste and set aside.  Deep-fry the beancurd dice until crispy brown, drain and set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(326,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(326,3,'Heat the 2 tbsp (30 ml) oil and fry the garlic golden brown.  Stir in the paste, add the lemon grass and coconut, stirring well.  Add all the vegetables and briefly stir-fry.  Add the stock, soy sauce and sugar. Stir well and turn on to a serving dish.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(326,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(326,5,'Source: The Lemon Grass Restaurant, Bangkok _Thai Vegetarian Cooking_ by Vatcharin Bhumichitr Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,1,'Place the quinoa in a large bowl; fill with cold water.  Drain into a strainer and repeat the rinsing and draining 4 more times.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,3,'Over medium-high heat, heat the oil in a 2-quart saucepan.  Add the rinsed quinoa and cook, stirring, until the quinoa makes cracking and popping noises, about 3 to 5 minutes.  Stir in the water, marjoram, thyme, and rosemary.  Bring to a boil, reduce the heat, and simmer, covered, 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,5,'Stir in the parsley, lemon juice, salt, lemon rind, and pepper.  Simmer, covered, 5 minutes longer.  Fluff with a fork.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,7,'Serves 4 to 6');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,9,'Calories:       206                     Total Fat:      3.2 g Protein:        6.0 g                   Saturated Fat:  1.2 g Carbohydrates: 33.0 g                   Cholesterol:    0 Fiber:          4.1 g                   Sodium:         451 mg');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,11,'Source: Wholesome Harvest - by Carol Gelles (ISBN: 0-316-30735-1)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(327,13,'Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(328,1,'Mix all ingredients together well & refrigerate till ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(328,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(328,3,'"Vegetarian Times Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(329,1,'Place first 6 ingredients in large soup pot.  Cover with 3 cups water & bring to a boil.  Cover & simmer for 7 to 8 minutes.  Add 2 more cups of water along with the rest of the ingredients.  Cover & simmer for 25 to 30 minutes.  Serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(329,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(329,3,'Nava Atlas, "Vegetariana"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(330,1,'1.Chop onion and carrot, saute in oil in a fairly large saucepan 2.Add all other ingredients - bring to boil 3.Simmer for 30 minutes, until liquid is absorbed 4.While 3. is taking place, preheat oven to 200C/400F/Gas Mark 6 5.Put mixture in loaf/flan dish 6.Put loaf/flan dish in 4. above. 7.Cook for 30 minutes');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(330,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(330,3,'Note:  I see no reason why you would need to use the oil, just cut up the carrots extra small, place  all ingredients in the pan and start at 2.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(330,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(330,5,'Posted by Pat Buttons');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,1,'Wash lentils thoroughly & pick out any sticks & stones & grit which might get in them.  In a large pot, bring the water to a rolling boil.  Add lentils & cook for 20-25 minutes until the lentils start to puree.  Drain & let cool. It is not necessary to let them get cold.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,3,'Transfer the cooked lentils to a large mixing bowl.   Add bread crumbs, garlic & onion & mix thoroughly.  Season well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,5,'You then can experiment with herbs & spices.  I usually add loads of cajun spice, with healthy measures of parsley, basil & majoram.  You could try thyme or sage.  It is your choice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,7,'If the mixture does not hold together well enough, add more bread crumbs. Form into patties & then cook as you would a regular hamburger in a little oil.  Or barbecue.  If they are really dry, then they hold together well enough to barbecue.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,9,'Serve in buns with old fashioned dijon mustard & chips ooops, errrr fries.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(331,11,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(332,1,'Wash lentils & drain.  Combine with 6 cups water, cinnamon stick, bay leaf, garlic cloves, ginger slices & turmeric. Bring to a boil, lower heat & simmer for 40 minutes, till lentils are tender & the water has been reduced significantly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(332,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(332,3,'Slice lemon thinly & add to the pot with salt, black pepper & cayenne. Simmer for a further 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(332,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(332,5,'Just before serving, heat ghee till hot, add asafetida & cumin seeds & saute till the seeds begin to colour.  Pour over top of dahl & serve over rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(332,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(332,7,'Madhur Jaffrey, "An Invitation to Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(333,1,'Rinze lentils thoroughly.  Cover with water & cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Add more water if you need to.  You should have a stiff puree.  Stir fry onions in a little oil till soft, throw in the cayenne & cook for a few more seconds.  Remove lentils from heat & stir in the remaining ingredients.  Add a little more stock or water if the mixture is too dry. Season with salt & pepper to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(333,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(333,3,'Grease a 1 lb loaf tin, press in the lentils mixture.  Bake at 375F/190C for 45 to 50 minutes.  Let stand for 10 minutes & then turn out on a plate.  Serve with vegetables.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(333,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(333,5,'Very loosely based on Sarah Brown, "Vegetarian Kitchen"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(334,1,'Cook lentils & onion in 2 c stock until tender but not mushy, about 25 minutes.  Drain excess water.  Heat oil in a skillet & saute bulgur & soy grits for 5 to 10 minutes.  Stir constantly.  Heat remaining stock, add to skillet & cook over a low heat till light & fluffy -- 10 minutes.  Let cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(334,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(334,3,'Mix yogurt, mayonnaise, garlic, mustard & lemon juice.  Combine grain with lentils & vegetables & toss in the dressing.  Chill if desired.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(334,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(334,5,'Frances Moore Lappe, "Diet for a Small Planet"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(335,1,'In a large pot, heat the oil over medium heat & add the garlic & onions. Saute for 2 minutes.  Add the celery, carrot & potatoes & saute for 8 minutes.  Add the tamari & the seasonings & continue to saute gently for another 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(335,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(335,3,'Add the stock, tomatoes & uncooked but washed lentils.  Bring to a boil, reduce heat & cook for 1 hour.  Stir frequently.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(335,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(335,5,'The lentils should puree, cook for longer if they need to puree more to thicken the soup.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(335,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(335,7,'"The Cookbook for People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(336,1,'Rinse lentils & soak for 30 minutes.  Heat half oil in skillet.  Add peppers & cook for 3 to 5 minutes till golden brown.  Drain & cool.  Add remaining oil to pan.  Cook cumin till they begin to pop.  Add onions & chilies & cook for 8 minutes.  Stir in ginger & coriander.  Drain lentils & add to the pan with water.  Stir well & cover.  Cook for 15 to 20 minutes til lthe liquid has evaporated.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(336,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(336,3,'Stir in salt & pepper.  Add cilantro.  Cut tops off peppers & remove seeds.  Stuff with the lentils & replace the tops.  Stand in a baking dish.  Bake at 350F for 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(336,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(336,5,'Linda Fraser, "Curries & Indian Foods"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,1,' This takes about 40 minutes to prepare: you can do "part 1" while "part 2" is cooking, plus about 1 hour to chill, then 15 minutes to cook.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,3,' Makes between 4 to 6 servings, depending on the size of patties you make and the hunger of participants.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,5,' Note: uncooked burgers may be individually wrapped and frozen.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,7,'Part 1:  Bring lentils and water to a boil in saucepan. Lower the heat, and simmer, partly-covered, 30 minutes, or until lentils are soft, and liquid is gone.  Place in large-ish bowl.  Add vinegar, and mash.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,9,'Part 2:  Saute remaining ingredients, except for wheat germ, together over medium-low heat 10 to 15 minutes, or until all is tender. Add to the mashed lentils, and mix well.  Add wheat germ and mix again. Chill for about 1 hour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,11,'The Burgers:');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,13,' 1. Make 4-inch patties from chilled burger-mixture.  For freezing, make patties, place wax paper between each patty and stack; wrap well and freeze (or wrap individually).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,15,' 2. Fry burgers in butter until brown, *or* broil about 8 minutes on each side.  Try putting sesame seeds in pan to keep burgers from sticking to pan, if it is a problem.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,16,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,17,' 3. Serve either as patties, or as burgers in a whole-wheat bun. Good with cheese melted on top, basil sprinkled on each burger is tasty also.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,18,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(337,19,'Mollie Katzen, "Moosewood Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,1,'Place lentils, water & turmeric in a pot over medium heat & bring to a boil.  Continue cooking, removing the froth from the top from time to time.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,3,'In a separate pot, heat half the ghee.  Saute onion & garlic till golden. Stir in ginger, chili & zucchini.  Mix thoroughly & continue to cook for 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,5,'Transfer the lentils to the zucchini mixture.  Stir in salt & garam masala.  Half cover the pot, lower the heat & cook for 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,7,'In the remaining ghee, toss in the cumin seeds & heat till they sizle & change colour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,9,'Serve lentils hot with the ghee/cumin seeds.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(338,11,'Michael Pandya, "Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(339,1,'NOTE on rice or soy milk: if it''s a thick milk, dilute it to the consistency of cow''s milk)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(339,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(339,3,'Simply mix all ingredients until all is blended.Dough will be very sticky.Divide evenly into 2 oiled or sprayed with Pam loaf pans.Allow to rise until doubled (it''s a pretty dense bread,but on a warm day,rising should be completed in about 4 hours) Bake in a preheated 375 degree oven for about 1 hour. Terrific for sandwiches or as a breakfast food!');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(339,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(339,5,'FROM:    L HERSHKOWITZ        (BDBG15B)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(340,1,'Wash lettuce & separate the leaves.  Allow to drain.  Beat the rest of the ingredients in a bowl.  Add lettuce leaves & turn them gently so that all the leaves become coated with the dressing.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(340,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(340,3,'Jack Santa Maria, Greek Vegetarian Cookery');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(341,1,'Put all ingredients into a saucepan.  Cover generously with water and bring to a boil.  Simmer, half-covered, for about 1 hour, then strain.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(341,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(341,3,'Other vegetables and flavorings, such as leeks, thinly pared lemon rind and allspice berries, can be added.  Peelings from well-scrubed potatoes also give a particularly pleasant flavor to vegetable stock.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(341,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(341,5,'Source: The Complete Vegetarian Cuisine - by Rose Elliot ISBN: 0-394-57123-1 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(342,1,'Cook lima beans in water according to packet instructions.  Steam carrots till tender.  Drain reserving cooking water.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(342,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(342,3,'Heat oil in a skillet & saute green onions & mushrooms until tender.  Add spices & saute for a further 1 minute.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(342,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(342,5,'Combine all ingredients (except milk) along with 1 cup of bean & carrot water.  Using a blender, blend in batches till smooth.  Pour mixture into a large soup pot.  Add milk. Cook slowly for 15 to 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(342,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(342,7,'Source Unknown');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,1,'Notes:');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,3,'For the mixed veg I use things like water chestnuts, green beans, cauliflower etc etc. The original recipe had pork and shrimp but I changed it, and it works fine :-)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,5,'Preparation:');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,7,'Slice the shallots lengthways Use brown sugar if palm sugar isn;t available. Peel and slice the cucumbers diagonally into thick ovals trim the green beans cut the cabbage into two inc wedges');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,9,'1. In a small, heavy bottomed saucepan, bring the coconut milk to a gentle');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,10,'   simmer over a low heat. Cook, stirring gently,until the coconut');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,11,'   milk is fragent and it''s oil glistens on the surface (about 6-8 mins)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,13,'2. While it simmers, combine the bean sauce and half of the shallots in');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,14,'   a mortar. Using a pestle, mash the mixture to a chunky paste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,15,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,16,'3. When the coconut milk is ready add the shallot paste and stir well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,17,'   Add all the vegetables except the cucumbers, cabbage,green beans and');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,18,'   the remaining shallots. Cook for five minutes');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,19,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,20,'4. Add the sugar and simmer until the shallots wilt and the sugar melts, 1');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,21,'   to 2 minutes. Add the tamarind and taste the sauce, which should be a');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,22,'   balance of salty, sour and sweet.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,23,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,24,'5. Transfer the sauce to a small bowl and place it on a plate, garnished');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,25,'   with the cucumbers, cabbage wedges and green beans. Serve warm or at');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,26,'   room temperature.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,27,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(343,28,'Shared by Kaz Glover');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(344,1,'Wash lentils & boil in water with salt, turmeric & tamarind over medium heat for 20 minutes.  Heat oil in a small pot.  Add cumin seeds & fry for a minute.  Stir in onion, garlic & ginger & fry till onion is browned & soft.  Add chili & stir fro 30 seconds.  Remove & pour over lentils, mix thoroughly & return to a boil.  Serve with rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(344,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(344,3,'Rani, "Feast of India"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(345,1,'In a small bowl, combine broth, hoisin sauce, rice wine or sherry, ketchup & hot sauce.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(345,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(345,3,'Place a wok over high heat, when hot, add vegetable oil.  Add garlic & stir for 5 seconds.  Add tofu & stir fry for 2 minutes.  Stir in reserved sauce & cook 1 minute.  Add bean sprouts & cook another minute.  Add dissolved cornstarch & stir till sauce thickens.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(345,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(345,5,'Serve over noodles tossed in sesame oil or over steamed rice..  Garnish with onions.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(345,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(345,7,'Madhur Jaffrey, "World of the East Vegetarian Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,1,'Heat a wok & coat with the oils.  Add garlic, leeks & red peppers.  Stir fry over high heat for 15 seconds.  Reduce heat to medium, add mushrooms & saute for 1 minute.  Add water, sake, soy sauce, salt, 7-spice pepper & ketchup.  Bring to a boil & cook for 30 seconds.  Add tofu & return to a boil.  Dissolve cornstarch in water & stir into the wok.  Simmer until thick.  Garnish with scallions.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,3,'* Or use minced scallions or onions');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,5,'# I substituted a sherry');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,7,'+ I used 1/4 ts of crushed chilies');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(346,9,'Shurtleff & Aoyagi, "The Book of Tofu"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(347,1,'Slice mushroom stems, leave the caps whole.  Place in a pot with a small amount of water & cook gently for 15 minutes.  Reserve the stock for soups.  Combine the remaining ingredients.  Place mushrooms in the marinade & let sit for at least 2 hours, either in the fridge or at room temperature, stirring ocassionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(347,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(347,3,'Adapted from Mollie Katzen, "Moosewood Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(348,1,'Rince, pat dry and slice mushrooms.  In a medium saucepan combine vinegar and mushrooms; bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered for 2 mins. Drain mushrooms; set aside to cool.  In a small saucepan bring water to boil. Add carrots & celery; return to boil. Reduce heat and simmer covered for 3 mins. Add red, green peppers; cover and simmer for 3 mins or until tender.  Drain and set aside to cool.  In medium bowl mix olive oil, oregano & salt, black pepper; let stand 10 mins.  Stir in mishrooms, carrots, and other vegetables.  Mix well.  Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hrs.  before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(348,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(348,3,'Lucinda Hollace Berry, "300 Sensational Salads"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(349,1,'Sift & mix the flour, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon & salt.  Add the oil & sugar.  Mix well.  Stir in the carrots & walnuts.  Enusre that all is well mixed.  Transfer to a greased cake tin approx. 20 cm X 20 cm. Bake at 350F for about an hour or until a knife inserted in the centre of the cake comes out clean.  Cool for a few minutes on a wire rack.  Turn out & let cool completely.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(349,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(349,3,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(350,1,'Combine all ingredients in a salad bottle.  Shake well.  If keeping in the fridge, remember to warm up to room temperature about an hour before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(350,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(350,3,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,1,'Ensure that the rice has been cooked ahead of time & is well cooled.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,3,'Heat about 2 to 3 tb vegetable oil in a wok.  When hot, add onions & garlic & fry for 3 minutes.  Add the carrots & stir-fry for 2 minutes. Add the rest of the vegetables & continue to stir-fry for 2 or 3 minutes. Toss in the chili pieces & ginger root.  Cook for a few seconds. Carefully stir in the cold rice.  Lower heat & continue to cook, stirring occasionally for 5 minutes.  Add enough soy sauce to coat the rice & cook for a further 5 minutes on low heat, stirring often to prevent sticking. Season if desired with salt & pepper.  Serve when heated through.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,5,'This goes great with spicy tofu dishes or works well on its own as a main dish in its own right.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,7,'If you desire something hotter, add more chili pieces. Use pieces rather than powder because they are hotter.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,9,'For a variation, I sometimes toss in a few strips of tofu just before adding the spices.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(351,11,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(352,1,'Wash peas well.  Place in a bowl, cover with hot water & let sit for an hour.  Drain.  Place in a large pot, add 4 1/2 cups water & throw in the turmeric.  Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.  Reduce heat to medium low, partially cover & simmer for 45 minutes.  Remove from heat, beat with a wire whisk till the mixture is finely pureed.  Stir in salt & set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(352,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(352,3,'When ready to serve, simmer puree over low heat till piping hot.  Heat ghee in a skillet over medium high heat.  When very hot, add cumin seeds & fry for 10 seconds.  Lower heat, add onions & fry for 20 minutes, stirring constantly to prevent burning.  Stir in red pepper & immediately pour in to the puree.  Garnish with coriander.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(352,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(352,5,'Serve with a potato dish, rice & bread.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(352,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(352,7,'Julie Sahni, "Classic Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(353,1,'Heat ghee in large pot.  Add onion & garlic & fry till browned.  Stir in ginger & fry for 2 minutes.  Add garam masala, turmeric & chili, stirring for a minute.  Stir in potatoes, salt & water.  Mix well, bring to a boil & simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.  Stir occasionally.  Add mushrooms & peas & stir.  Cook, covered, for 5 to 8 minutes.  Remove lid, raise heat & cook till 3/4 of water has evaporated.  Stirring constantly.  Serve with dal.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(353,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(353,3,'Rani, "Feast of India"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(354,1,'Wash lentils.  Place in a deep pot with the turmeric & 5 cups of water. Bring to a bol, stirring often.  Reduce heat to medium-low & simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.  Turn off heat & beat lentils with a wire whisk to smooth the puree.  Stir in the salt.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(354,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(354,3,'When ready to serve, simemr the puree till pi[ping hot.  Heat the ghee in a skillet.  When hot, add garlic slices & fry till they start to turn brown.  Pour this over the lentil puree.  Stir to mix & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(354,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(354,5,'Julie Sahni, "Classic Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(355,1,'Boil potatoes at least 2 hours ahead.  Leave to cool.  Just before cooking the dish, cube them into bite-sized pieces.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(355,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(355,3,'Heat oil over a medium flame.  Fry potatoes in small batches till golden brown on all sides.  Drain & set aside.  Save some of the oil for later use.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(355,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(355,5,'Blend onion & garlic with 3 tb water.  Heat 6 tb oil in large pot.  When very hot, add asafetida, fenugreek, fennel, onion, & mustard seeds & bay leaf & red pepper in quick succession.  Fry 20 seconds till bay leaf darkens.  Add paste from the blender & turmeric.  Fry, stirring for 5 minutes.  Add tomatoes & sugar.  Gently stir in 2 c water, salt & potatoes.  Bring to a boil.  Cover & simer for 10 minutes.  Turn each potato over & simmer another 10 minutes.  Serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(355,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(355,7,'Madhur Jaffrey, "An Invitation to Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,1,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. In a large saucepan, heat oil and saute onions until lightly browned.  Add the TVP mince, stir and cook for two minutes.  Pour the hot water or stock over the saute and simmer for four minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,3,'In a separate bowl, mix the breadcrumbs, herbs and garlic together with one cup cold water.  Stir in the egg and leave to one side for ten minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,5,'Combine the cooked TVP mince with the breadcrumbs mixture, then add the soy sauce.  Stir well and season to taste.  Using your hands, shape the mixture into an oval mound and place it in the center of a large baking dish, leaving plenty of space all around for the tomato sauce to run.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,7,'Heat the tomatoes, tomato paste and seasoning in a small saucepan, and pour over the loaf, then bake for one hour.  Serves 6.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,9,'JTK''s notes:  I usually add more herbs & chopped garlic, and saute chopped vegetables like celery, carrots, and/or mushrooms after onions are done but before adding TVP. Hot sauce is a good addition, too, or other flavored sauce like veg. Worcestershire. The egg replacer works fine --- not sure if it''s even necessary. Also, I make the tomato sauce differently (sometimes I use canned/jar or homemade frozen sauce, and I prefer canned whole tomatoes, pureed, to prechopped ones), but it doesn''t matter much. I make breadcrumbs from whatever bread is available, preferably wholewheat (lightly toasted for dryness) --- doesn''t matter much either. Cracker crumbs would probably do as well, if you don''t have bread around or a food processor/blender.  I''ve made 1.5x recipe into a single loaf OK, but larger wouldn''t work (would have to make separate loaves, if larger quantities are desired)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,11,'makes 1 loaf, approx. 6x10" (fits comfortably into a 9x13" pan with a couple inches margin around for sauce --- see above). VEGAN/OVO.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(356,13,'(orig. posted by Jean Reese, adapted from Veg. Times)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(357,1,'""NOTE: After a couple of hours, the croutons will start to absorb the dressing. Some people like this; others (including the reviewer for Toronto Life!) do not. Time the addition of the croutons to suit your taste."');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(357,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(357,3,'Preheat oven to 350F. Spread the bread cubes on a large baking sheet & toss with the oil. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown, turning them every few minutes. They will take 10 to 20 minutes, depending on how fresh the bread is. Assemble the cucumber, peppers, green onion and parsley in a large bowl; leave out the tomatoes for now. Prepare the dressing: Stir the lemon juice, salt and garlic together until the salt dissolves. Add the pepper, cinnamon and allspice, then slowly beat in the olive oil. (May be prepared up to 12 hours ahead to this point.) Place the cut up tomatoes on top of the other vegetables. Pour on the dressing and toss well; add the croutons and toss again (see note).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(357,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(357,5,'David Wood "The David Wood Food Book"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(358,1,'Mix all ingredients together & chill at least one hour before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(358,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(358,3,'"New Recipes From Moosewood Restaurant"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,1,'Gently fry spring onion in 1/4 cup olive oil for 2-3 minutes.  Turn into a bowl and add remaining stuffing ingredients, adding salt and pepper to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,3,'Remove leaves from cabbage carefully so as not to tear them, counting larger leaves as 2.  Par-boil cabbage leaves in boiling water until limp enough to handle, cooking leaves in 2 to 3 lots.  Drain in a colander.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,5,'Cut out larger part of centre rib in each leaf and cut larger leaves in half down centre.  Line base of a deep pan with ribs and any torn leaves.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,7,'Place a generous tablespoon stuffing on base of each leaf, roll up once and tuck in sides to contain filling.  Roll to end of leaf.  Repeat with remaining ingredients.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,9,'Crush garlic with salt and blend in crumbled, crushed mint and lemon juice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,11,'Pack rolls flap side down in lined pan, sprinkling some of the garlic-lemon mixture and olive oil between layers of rolls.  Invert a plate on top of the rolls to keep them intact during cooking.  Add enough cold water to just cover rolls and put lid on firmly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,13,'Bring to the boil on medium heat, reduce to low and simmer gently for 45 minutes.  Remove from heat and leave aside for 30 minutes.  Serve lukewarm or cold.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(359,15,'Source: The Complete Middle East Cookbook - by Tess Mallos Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(360,1,'Wash millet and drain with a fine mesh strainer until water comes clean. Place millet in a heavy pot and add cooking water. Let soak 4-8 hours or overnight before cooking.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(360,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(360,3,'Add salt and diced turnips. Bring to a boil, place heat deflector under the pot, then simmer over low flame for 45-50 minutes. For a creamier texture, allow millet to sit in the pot 10 minutes before uncovering. Mash with a potato masher; if necessary, add a cup of water while mashing to make a mashed potato consistency. Transfer to a serving bowl and cover. Serve with an ice cream scoop and top with gravy.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(360,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(360,5,'Total calories per serving: 207  Fat: 2 grams');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(360,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(360,7,'From the Vegetarian Journal  Nov/Dec 1992,page 7 From: Susan Grabowski');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(361,1,'Preheat oven to 350F.  Bring water to a boil & add the millet.  Cook over medium heat for 25 minutes or till the water is absorbed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(361,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(361,3,'Heat oil in a skillet over medium-high heat.  Add onions, peppers, celery & fresh garlic.  Saute for 5 minutes.  Add seasonings & cook for a further 2 minutes.  Mix into the millet.  Add tahini & wheat germ & half the tomato sauce.  Mix well & season to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(361,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(361,5,'Shape into an 8" x 12" loaf pan.  Pour over remaining sauce, sprinkle yeast on top & bake for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(361,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(361,7,'"The Cookbook for People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,1,'You can serve this versatile loaf for lunch or as an appetizer.  Place slices on a bed of Bibb lettuce with vegetable garnishes and a light, creamy salad dressing.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,2,'     ************************************************************');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,3,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,4,'Rinse the millet and put it in a medium saucepan with the water and 1/2 teaspoon sea salt.  Cook the millet, covered, over medium heat for about 30 minutes or until soft; the millet should absorb all of the water.  (If the grains are too moist, the loaf will not bind properly.)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,5,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,6,'Saute the carrots, celery, onions, and garlic in oil for 6 minutes, or until the onions are translucent.  Add the seasonings, including the remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons of salt.  Mix the cooked millet and the vegetables together, along with the nuts or seeds, if you wish.  Mix the two flours together and add them to the millet mixture, blending it well so the loaf will hold together.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,7,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,8,'Lightly oil and flour a large loaf pan.  Press the millet mixture into the pan and bake in a preheated oven at 400 degrees F for about one hour.  (If the millet mixture is warm when you put it in the pan, reduce the baking time to about 45 minutes.)  Allow the loaf to cool for 10 minutes, then carefully remove it from the pan.  To avoid breaking the loaf, you may wish to slice it while it is still in the pan.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,9,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(362,10,'Source: Friendly Foods - by Brother Ron Pickarski, O.F.M. ISBN: 0-89815-377-8 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(363,1,'Combine all dry ingredients in a medium bowl. Mix all liquid ingredients together, then add to dry ingredients. Put mixture in well oiled muffin tins (makes 12 muffins. You can also make a loaf bread from this.) Bake at 375(F) for 15-20 minutes (35-40 for loaf) or until done.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(363,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(363,3,'This recipe comes from Arrowhead Mills Posted by: kupstas@cs.unc.edu (Eileen Kupstas)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(364,1,'Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a soup pot and toast millet until golden brown and beginning to pop.  Remove from heat, add 1-1/2 cups water, bring to a boil, and simmer for 20 minutes.  In a medium skillet, heat oil and saute celery, green pepper, onion, garlic, and carrot until onion is translucent.  To millet pot add 6 cups water (for thick soup), cauliflower, bay leaf, sauteed mixture, soup base, and herbs and celery seed.  Simmer for 20 minutes.  In a blender, process miso, cashews, 1 cup water, and yeast.  Add to soup and simmer 10 minutes.  Taste for salt and adjust consistency with more water if you like. Makes 2 quarts');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(364,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(364,3,'Source: Diet for a Small Planet, by Frances Moore Lappe. Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(365,1,'Cut eggplants into 1 cm thick slices & layer them in a colander with the salt.  Let them drain for 30 minutes.  Wash them under cold water & dry them on paper towels.  Beat together oil, lemon juice, mint, cumin, garlic & pepper.  Beat together, separately, the yogurt, mint & cumin.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(365,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(365,3,'Heat the grill to high.  Lay the eggplant slices on the hot rack & brush them with half the lemon mixture.  Grill them until they begin to brown. This will take about 2 minutes.  Turn over, brush with the rest of the lemon mixture & brown.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(365,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(365,5,'Serve grilled eggplants hot with the sauce separately as an appetizer.  Or place the eggplant on a large platter & spoon the sauce over the top & serve as a vegetable accompaniment for middle eastern dishes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(365,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(365,7,'Gail Duff, "A Book of Herbs & Spices"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,1,'In a small saucepan, whisk together arrowroot and water.  Heat and add miso, mirin, plum sauce and brown sugar.  Stir and continue cooking until thickened, about 5 minutes.  Remove from heat and let cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,3,'Slice each eggplant in half lengthwise and trim ends from green onions. Wipe shiitake mushrooms with a damp towel to remove dirt.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,5,'Brush grill with oil to prevent sticking.  Cook tofu over medium-hot coals 7 to 8 minutes each side until edges start to crisp.  While tofu grills, place whole green onions, shiitake mushrooms and eggplant (cut-side down) on grill and cook 5 minutes.  Turn and baste with miso sauce.  Continue cooking 5 to 8 minutes until eggplant can be pierced easily with a fork. Serve with extra sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,7,'Per serving: Calories: 398           Grams of Fat: 16           %Fat Calories: 36 Cholesterol: 0 mg       Grams of Fiber: 6');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(366,9,'Source: Delicious! Magazine, July/August 1993 Typos provided by: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(367,1,'In a medium skillet, heat oil.  Add scallions & garlic & saute for 3 minutes.  Transfer to a medium bowl.  Add miso.  Slowly add 1 cup stock stirring well all the time.  Add more liquid if you want a thinner sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(367,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(367,3,'"Vegetarian Times, April 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(368,1,'In a large pot, heat the oil over medium high heat.  Add the garlic & onions & saute for 2 minutes.  Add the carrots & celelry & saute for another 5 minutes.  Add the stock, mixed vegetables & herbs & spices. Cook for 1 hour.  Add the shells & continue to cook till tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(368,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(368,3,'Dilute the miso in 1 cup warm stock.  Add to the soup & simmer for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(368,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(368,5,'"The Cookbook for People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,1,'Preheat oven to 275F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,3,'Grease a 10" bundt pan & srinkle with cocoa (don''t ask what a bundt pan is).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,5,'Sift together flour, baking soda & salt.  Heat coffee & brandy on low for 5 minutes.  Add chocolate & margarine & stir till melted.  Add sugar & stir till dissolved.  Let cool & then transfer to a large mixing bowl. Add flour mixture about 1/2 cup at a time.  Beat till smooth.  Add eggs & vanilla & beat for a minute.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,7,'Pour batter into the pan.  Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until it is cooked. Allow to cool in the pan for 10 minutes.  Invert onto a plate & remove pan when completely cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(369,9,'Adapted from "New Recipes From Moosewood Restaurant"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,1,'Combine grains in a mixing bowl and set aside. Pour the oil into a 2-3 qt. casserole which is safe for both stovetop and oven cooking, and place on med. heat. When hot , saute onion and garlic until tender and translucent, about 5-6 mins. Add the mixed grains and saute for 1 min., stirring constantly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,3,'Meanwhile melt butter or margarine (if using) in a separate pan on med. high heat. When hot , add mushrooms and saute quickly, stirring frequently, until the shrooms are hot and have just absorbed the "butter" (about 1 min.). Immediately remove from heat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,5,'Add the broth, herbs, and mushrooms to the casserole with the onions and grains, and bring to a boil. Season with salt and pepper to taste, cover tightly (use aluminum foil between pot and cover if necessary for a good seal), and bake at 350 degrees F for 1 hr.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,7,'NOTES: I use alot less oil (only as much as needed to keep things from sticking in my cast-iron dutch oven), add hot peppers and fresh herbs (rosemary is especially delicious; i dislike dried oregano so i use less or none), add soy sauce instead of salt, and saute the mushrooms first in the same pan (taking them out when done) so i dont have to wash two pans :^>. Frankly i can''t see where they get 8 servings from, this lasts me maybe 3 meals....It''s really a hearty dish, so save it for a cold day (some of us still have a few left, despite the advent of spring). Enjoy!');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,9,'(8 servings as a side dish, less as an entree)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(370,11,'From: karpen@nrlfs1.nrl.navy.mil (Judy Karpen) @Newsgroups: rec.food.veg');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,1,'Place the cauliflower, potatoes, fresh peas & green beans in the bottom of a pot & cover with water.  Put the carrots, beets & celery in a steaming basket, cover & place over the pot.  Cook until the vegetables are tender-crisp.  Drian, saving the water.  Add the frozen peas, defrosted first, to the steamed vegetables.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,3,'In a blender, while it is running, drop in the chilies.  Add the chick peas, nuts & seeds & process until the peas are mashed.  Some vegetable water may facilitate this.  Add the cauliflower, potatoes, fresh peas, if using, & beans.  Pulse on & off till they are coarsely mashed.  Transfer to a mixing bowl, add the steamed vegetables, salt, pepper, turmeric & garam masala.  Mix well.  Divide into portions.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,5,'Line a baking sheet with waxed paper.  Flatten a portion into an almond shaped cutlet, 1/2 inch thick & place on the sheet.  Cover & refrigerate for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,7,'Whisk the soy milk, cornstarch & flour in a flat bowl until smooth.  Dip each cutlet into the batter, roll in poppy seeds & set aside briefly to air dry.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,9,'Heat ghee to a depth of 3/4 inch.  Without crowding, fry the cutlets in batches for 2 minutes each side.  Drain & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(371,11,'Adapted from Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(372,1,'Clean and wash the lentils and boil them until tender.  Mash and strain into a separate pot.  Add the rice, salt, and spices, and mix well.  In a pan, saute the chopped onions in oil until golden.  Add them with the frying oil to the lentils and rice.  Bring the mixture to the boil with enough water to cover and simmer over low heat for about 10 minutes, until the rice is cooked, stirring regularly to prevent sticking.  Serve lukewarm or cold with radishes and spring onions or a cabbage salad.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(372,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(372,3,'That''s the recipe straight from the book.  I make a couple changes: first of all, I''m a bit liberal with the cumin and allspice - I don''t use measuring spoons, and I''m sure I get more than the 1/4 or 1/2 teaspoon. Bhar, btw, is described by the book as "a spice blend made of cloves, cinnamon and nutmeg.  It is very similar in flavor to allspice, which may be substituted for it."  I use brown basmati rice, so I have to boil it for more than 10 minutes; this means I have to keep adding water to it so it doesn''t dry out.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(372,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(372,5,'I mean to go back to the restaurant I first had this dish at and ask them what spices they use, since theirs is both spicier and darker than mine.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(372,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(372,7,'Food For The Vegetarian - Traditional Lebanese Recipes From: bobp@msi.com (Bob Pitha)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(373,1,'Bring lentils & water to a boil.  Reduce heat, cover & simmer for 25 minutes.  Heat 2 tb oil in a skillet & saute onions & salt till the onions are transulcent.  Heat remaining oil in another skillet & saute the rice for 3 minutes.  Combine lentils, rice & onion, cover tightly & simmer till the lentils & rice are render, about 1 hour.  You may have to add up to 2 extra cups water.  Stir occasionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(373,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(373,3,'Serve with a green salad.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(373,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(373,5,'Frances Moore Lappe, "Diet for a Small Planet"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,1,'Pre-heat oven to 350F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,3,'Blend the honey, water, oil, tahini.  Blend in coffee substitute.  Add tofu chunks, one at a time.  Mix till creamy.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,5,'Lightly oil 9" pie pan.  Sprinkle in cracker crumbs.  Pour in half the tofu mixture.  Drizzle chocolate glaze over it.  Cover with the rest of the tofu.  Gently insert a knife into the pie & pull up the chocolate, making swirling designs.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,7,'Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(374,9,'"Vegetarian Times", April 1991');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(375,1,'Blend it all in the food processor until smooth.  I do everything separately, then mix it all together because my food processor is not big enough to do it all at once.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(375,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(375,3,'Serve as a sandwich spread, or on crackers.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(375,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(375,5,'This recipe makes *a lot*.  I think it freezes well, just stir well after it thaws, and make sure the lentils and green beans are well drained. Serve with crackers or make sandwiches with it.  This recipe makes quite a lot of spread.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(375,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(375,7,'From: tracy@telesoft.com (Tracy E. Childs @tesla) @Newsgroups: rec.food.veg');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(376,1,'    Sprinkle potatoes with flour and deep-fry until golden.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(376,2,' Drain and set aside. Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the oil, reheat an add onion. Stir-fry 10 seconds and add snow peas and wood ears. Stir-fry another 10 seconds and add salt, sugar and water. Bring to rapid boil, stirring constantly, and cook until peas are just tender crisp. Add reserved fried potato slices, heat through and serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(376,3,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(376,4,'    Wood ears are a type of mushroom or shelf fungus. When soaked it has a crunchy, gelatinous texture with little taste. If you can''t find them, I imagine that you could use the dried mushrooms although they wouldn''t give exactly the same effect. A closer substitute would be dried jellyfish, but if you''re some- where that sells dried jellyfish, I''m sure that they have wood ears as well...');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(376,5,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(376,6,'    From "The Regional Cooking of China" by Margaret Gin and Alfred E. Castle. 101 Productions, San Francisco, 1975. From: Stephen Ceideburg');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(377,1,'Bill tofu in water for 10 minutes. Drain the tofu and let it cool. Blend the tofu and the rest of the ingredients into a blender or food processor until smooth. If the "whipped cream" is too thick, add soymlk sparingly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(377,2,' Chill at least 1 hour before serving. Makes 1 cup.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(377,3,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(377,4,'DEEANNE                      at 14:51 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(378,1,'Heat ghee in a pot.  Add ginger, garlic & onion & stir-fry 1 minute.  Add garam masala, turmeric & chili powder.  Stir-fry for 30 seconds.  Add tomatoes & stir-fry for 3 minutes.  Add water.  Bring to a boil, reduce heat & simmer 5 minutes.  Add vinegar, soy sauce, salt & pepper.  Mix well.  Garnish with green onions & cilantro.  Serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(378,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(378,3,'Adapted from Betty Jung, "The Kopan Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(379,1,'Pour flour in a mound on the counter.  Make a whole in the centre. Sprinkle in salt & baking powder.  Add 1/2 the water & with your hand, mix the water & the flour.  Add the rest of the water & continue to work until the dough is smooth.  Knead well for 5 minutes.  Cover & set aside for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(379,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(379,3,'Knead dough on well floured surface.  Roll into a long sausage shape about 1" in diameter.  Cut into pieces 1" wide.  Dust with flour & flatten each piece into a round.  Roll each round with your hands until you have a perfect circle of 3" to 3 1/2" & the thickness of a coin.  Fill with the filling of your choice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(379,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(379,5,'Betty Jung, "The Kopan Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(380,1,'Preheat the oven to 325 F.  Wrap pancakes in foil and place in oven to warm, about 8 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(380,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(380,3,'Heat sesame oil in a wok or large skillet until very hot.  Add green onions, bok choy, red bell pepper, carrots and mushrooms.  Stir-fry vegetables 3 to 4 minutes until crisp tender.  Add sprouts, tofu, ginger and garlic and continue cooking 2 to 3 minutes until sprouts are soft. Stir in tamari and extra hoisin sauce.  To eat, drizzle a spoonful of hoisin sauce across center of pancake.  Top with generous helping of vegetables and roll up burrito style.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(380,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(380,5,'Per Serving: Calories: 345           Grams of Fat: 10.5 % Fat calories: 27      Cholesterol: 0 mg               Grams of Fiber 7');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(380,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(380,7,'Source: Delicious!  July/August 1993 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(381,1,'Beat shortening for 30 seconds.  Add sugar & beat till light & fluffy. Add molasses & water.  Mix well.  Add the baking soda, cinnamon, ginger & salt.  Mix.  Finally fold in flour.  Mix well.  Form into 1 inch balls. Place on a greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.  Flatten slightly & bake at 375F for 8 to 10 minutes.  Cool on a wire rack.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(381,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(381,3,'Makes 36.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(381,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(381,5,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(382,1,'GARNISH: toasted sesame seeds, minced scallions, finely chopped tomatoes, or Herbed Garlic Croutons, optional In 4-5 qt saucepan, heat oil. Add carrots, garlic, and onion; cook until tender. Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(382,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(382,3,'Meanwhile, in food processor, puree chick peas, 1 cup of vegetable stock, tahini, and lemon juice.  Stir pureed mixture into saucepan.  Add remaining ingredients including vegetable stock.  Cover and cook for 5 minutes to heat through.  Top with garnish if desired.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(382,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(382,5,'VARIATIONS: - substitute olive oil for safflower oil');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(382,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(382,7,'Source Unknown.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(383,1,'For the stew: In a 4-quart saucepan, heat the oil over medium-high heat. Add the onion and garlic, and cook, stirring, until softened.  Add 1/2 tsp. of the salt and all of the cinnamon, ginger, tumeric, nutmeg, and red pepper, stirring until absorbed.  Add the water and cloves; bring to a boil.  Add the carrot, squash, chickpeas, sweet potato, raisins, apricots, and brown sugar, and return to a boil.  Reduce the heat and simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, 40 to 45 minutes, or until the sweet potato is tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(383,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(383,3,'For the couscous: During the last 5 minutes of cooking the stew, place the couscous in a medium-sized bowl.  Add the boiling water and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.  Let stand 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(383,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(383,5,'Serve the stew over the couscous and top with the chopped almonds.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(383,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(383,7,'Source: Wholesome Harvest - by Carol Gelles (ISBN: 0-316-30735-1) Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,1,'Wash rice & soak for 30 minutes.  Slice eggplant into rounds & soak in slightly salted water.  Peel & cut potatoes into rounds.  Put rice in a pan with the tomatoes, garlic, onion, salt & pepper.  Add 2 c water & allow to simmer gently until the water has been absorbed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,3,'Dry the eggplants & fry in the olive oil until they just begin to turn golden.  Put side.  Fry the potatoes in the same way.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,5,'Make the white sauce.  In a pot, heat the ghee.  Gradually stir in the flour, then the soya milk.  Add a pinch of salt, pepper & nutmeg.  Simmer gently for 1 minute.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,7,'Grease a casserole dish.  Put in a layer of potatoes, followed by eggplant & finally the rice mixture.  Space out the allspice berries on the top. Add the sauce.  Bake at 375F for about 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(384,9,'Adapted from Jack Santa Maria, "Greek Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(385,1,'In a 2-cup measuring cup, combine water and sugar.  Stir in yeast.  Let stand until foamy, 5 to 10 minutes.  In a food processor fitted with the steel blade, combine 3 cups flour, salt and shortening.  Add yeast mixture. Process until dough forms a ball, about 5 seconds.  Stop machine; check consistency of dough.  It should be smooth and satiny.  If dough is too dry, add more warm water, 1 tablespoon at a time, processing just until blended.  If dough is too sticky, add more flour, 1 or 2 tablespoons at a time, processing just until blended.  Process 20 seconds to knead. Lightly oil a large bowl, swirling to coat bottom and sides. Place dough in oiled bowl; turn to coat all sides.  Cover bowl with plastic wrap. Let rise in a warm, draft-free place until doubled in bulk, about 1-1/2 hours. Lightly grease a baking sheet.  When dough has doubled in bulk, punch down dough; turn out onto a lightly floured surface.  Form dough into a round loaf about 10 inches in diameter; place on greased baking sheet. Sprinkle top of loaf with sesame seeds; press seeds gently into surface of loaf. Cover very loosely with plastic wrap; let rise until almost doubled in bulk, 1 hour. Place rack in centre of oven. Preheat oven to 425F. Remove plastic wrap. Bake loaf in centre of preheated oven 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 375F; bake 25 minutes.  The loaf is done when it sounds hollow when tapped on bottom. Cool completely on a rack before slicing. makes 1 loaf.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(385,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(385,3,'Posted by Rich Harper in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,1,'Soak, rinse & cook chick peas.  Cook for 45-60 minutes till soft, depending on age of the peas.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,3,'In a soup pot, saute the onions in the ghee for 5 minutes.  Add chili, cayenne, turmeric & coriander.  Saute for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring.  Add the stock & the vegetables.  Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.  Add the coconut, coconut milk, chick peas & cook for a further 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,5,'Remove from heat & let cool for a few minutes.  Blend well.  Return to pot & add lemon juice & cilantro.  The longer this soup sits, the better its flavour.  Re-heat gently & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,7,'There are many variations on Mulligatawny Soup.  This is mine that omits the traditional chicken stock but adds the occasionally used chick peas.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(386,9,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(387,1,'Clean & wash dahl.  Place in a heavy pot.  Add 5 c water & bring to a boil.  Reduce heat & remove froth.  Add garlic, ginger, cilantro, turmeric & cayenne.  Cover, leaving lid slightly ajar & cook for 1 1/2 hours.  Stir occasionally.  When cooked, add salt & lemon juice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(387,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(387,3,'In a skillet, heat ghee til lhot.  Add asafetida & a few seconds later, add the cumin.  When the cumin seeds darken, remove from heat & add to the cooked dahl & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(387,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(387,5,'Madhur Jaffrey, "An Invitation to Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(388,1,'Wash mung beans.  Place with turmeric & ginger in a large pot.  Add 4 cups water & bring to a boil, stirring often.  Reduce heat to medium & simmer, partially covered, for 30 minutes.  Turn off heat & beat with a wire whisk.  When ready to serve, heat puree till piping hot.  Stir in the lemon juice & salt.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(388,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(388,3,'Heat ghee over a high heat in small frying pan.  When very hot, carefully add the mustard seeds & fry till they start to turn grey.  When they stop sputtering, add the chili.  Stir rapidly for a monent & then turn off the heat.  Pour over the puree & fold in the chopped coriander.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(388,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(388,5,'This dal is excellent with almost every vegetable.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(388,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(388,7,'Julie Sahni, "Classic Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(389,1,'Heat oil in a medium sized skillet & saute vegetables & garlic till limp. In a large bowl, crumble or mash tofu.  Add sauteed vegetables, yeast & salt.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(389,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(389,3,'Pre-heat oven to 350F.  Spread tofu mixture evenly into a 9 1/2" or 10" quiche pan.  Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, till the edges start to brown. Garnish with tomatoes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(389,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(389,5,'"Vegetarian Times" March, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(390,1,'Heat olive oil in a large frying pan & cook the garlic, parsley & marjoram for 1 minute.  Add sliced mushrooms & cook over moderate heat for 5 minutes.  Add tomatoes, salt & pepper.  Cook over high heat for 8 to 10 minutes or until the sauce starts to thicken.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(390,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(390,3,'Serve over 1lb pasta.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(390,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(390,5,'Paolo Gavin, "Italian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,1,'Heat oil or white grape juice in a medium-sized skillet. Saute vegetables and garlic until limp. In a large bowl, crumble or mash tofu. Add sauteed vegetables, and yeast and salt if desired.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,3,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees (325 if using glass pan). Spread tofu mixture evenly into a 9 or 10-inch quiche pan. Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until the edges of the tofu start to brown. Garnish with tomatoes. Serves 6-8.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,5,'Variation: If you prefer quiche with a crust, use your favorite single pie crust recipe.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,7,'From _Vegetarian Times_, March, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(391,9,'A.BROADDUS [Alice in Hou]    at 10:19 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(392,1,'Soak mushrooms in water for 20 minutes.  Separate stem from caps & discard stems.  Heat oil in a soup pot & fry onion, garlic & ginger for 2 minutes. Add soy sauce, sugar & salt.  Mix together well.  Pour in stock & simmer gently with the lid on for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(392,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(392,3,'Jack Santa Maria, "Chinese Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,1,'In a large skillet, heat the oil.  Saute the leeks and garlic for 2 minutes, stirring frequently.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,3,'Add the mushrooms, oregano, salt, and black pepper.  Reduce the heat slightly and continue to cook, stirring occasionally, until the mushrooms are cooked and their liquid has evaporated, about 5 to 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,5,'Puree in a blender or food processor and stir in lemon juice and horseradish to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,7,'Variation: Before pureeing, this combination makes a fine filling for turnovers; if necessary, you can stretch the amount by blending in some mashed tofu and additional seasonings.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,9,'Makes 1-1/4 cups');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(393,11,'Source: Recipes from an Ecological Kitchen - by Lorna J. Sass ISBN: 0-688-10051-1 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,1,'Taking each mushroom as a rough circle cut towards centre in a spiral to make one long strip as if peeling an apple in one go.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,3,'THE MARINADE: In a mortar pound together the galangal, lemon grass, lime leaf, coriander roots and garlic to form a paste.  Place this in a mixing bowl and stir in all the other ingredients, mixing well.  Place all the mushroom strips in this marinade and leave for at least 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,5,'PEANUT SAUCE: In a wok or frying pan/skillet, heat the oil, add the curry paste and fry briefly until it blends with the oil.  Add the coconut milk, lower the heat and stir well until a rich red colour appears.  Add the remaining ingredients, stirring constantly until a thick sauce is formed, and set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,7,'Take the mushroom strips from the marinade and thread each one on to a satay stick.  Grill/broil until cooked through.  Serve with the peanut sauce and fresh cucumber pickle.  Little triangles of toast may also be served for those who wish to mop up more sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(394,9,'Source: Thai Vegetarian Cooking by Vatcharin Bhumichitr Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(395,1,'Saute mushrooms & garlic in oil till soft.  Stir in the remaining ingredients & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(395,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(395,3,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(396,1,'Heat safflower in a wok.  When hot add garlic & onion & saute over moderately low heat till the onion is translucent.  Add mushrooms, bell pepper, wine, tamari, ginger & sesame oil.  Mix.  Reduce heat, cover & simmer till mushrooms are tender but not overdone.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(396,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(396,3,'Dissolve cornstarch in a small amount of water & stir into skillet.  Stir in tofu, cover & simmer for another 2 minutes.  Serve over noodles garnished with almonds.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(396,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(396,5,'Nava Atlas, "Vegetariana"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(397,1,'Rice:  place rice, water, soy sauce and scallions in a saucepan with a tight-fitting lid.  Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and cook over medium heat until liquid has evaporated and rice is tender, about 1 hour. Set aside. Mushrooms:  Place onion, celery and water in a large pan. Cook and stir for several minutes, until vegetables soften slightly. Add buttom, shittake and oyster mushrooms, cook, stirring occasionally, for 10 minutes. Gently stir in cooked rice, enoki mushrooms, snow peas, red pepper and seasonings.  Cook over low heat for another 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(397,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(397,3,'A.ENGLISH [Al & Diane]       at 21:48 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,1,'Rinse tofu and pat dry.  Cube and puree in food processor with all ingredients except cima mix.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,3,'Shape the cima mix into a 12" by 3" roll.  Sread the tofu puree on a 12" by 28" piece of plastic wrap and roll around the cima log.  Smooth out the seam. Steam 30 minutes, let cool 10 minutes, slice and serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,5,'Note:  you MUST have a steamer wide enough to support the entire roll from underneath!  If you don''t, it will slip and come unrolled.  It''ll still get cooked, but rather than a pretty, colorful roll to slice you''ll have a serious mess.  This shouldn''t be a problem, but for a broke person cooking for nine @someone else''s apartment, these harware problems have a nasty way of only becoming apparently an hour before mealtime. (sigh)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,7,'CIMA MIX: (makes 4 1/2C  Bro Ron suggests using the extra for ''meatballs'' or something.  Far be it from me to argue w/my hero, but remember to use a big enough skillet.)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,9,'Saute onions in oil until translucent.  Remove from heat.  Add bread crumbs, tofu, seitan, soy grits, nut yeast, water and seasoning.  Mix until evenly dispersed. Add vegs and nuts.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,11,'In a separate bowl, mix agar and gluten flour.  Heat lecithin and stir into veg mixture, then stir in flour/agar mixture.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,13,'(from Friendly Foods, serves 4)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(398,15,'From: mad4@ellis.uchicago.edu (Bill Maddex)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(399,1,'Heat 2 tbsp (30 ml) of the oil until a light haze forms, then fry half the shallots and half the garlic until crispy brown.  Drain and set aside, keeping the oil for the Fried Dry Chilis.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(399,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(399,3,'Drain the moong beans, place in a mortar, pound well to form a paste and set aside.  In the mortar, pound together the coriander roots with the remaining shallots and garlic until a paste forms, then set aside. In a frying pan or wok heat the remaining unused oil, stir in the red curry paste and cook.  Add half the coconut milk, stirring well, add the paste of coriander root, shallot and garlic and thoroughly mix.  Add in the moong bean paste and stir well.  Add the soy sauce, sugar and tamarind juice, lemon juice and chili powder, stirring constantly.  Put the two halves of the kaffir lime into the mixture and continue to cook gently. Thin the remaining coconut milk with the water then stir in to the sauce and boil.  Simmer for 1 minute.  Quickly stir in the crispy shallot and garlic mix and immediately turn into a serving bowl.  Save the remaining oil for the side dish.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(399,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(399,5,'FRIED DRY CHILIS: Re-heat the oil and quickly stir-fry the chilis.  Turn into a small serving bowl.  Serves three.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(399,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(399,7,'Source: Thai Vegetarian Cooking by Vatcharin Bhumichitr Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(400,1,'Mix together flour, molasses, salt & oil.  Proof yeast in 1 cup of lukewarm water.  Let sit for 10 minutes.  Add to flour mixture.  Mix in the rest of the water, a little at a time, until the dough is firm & not too sticky.  Turn out onto lightly floured board & knead for 15 minutes. Place in large, lightly oiled bowl, cover with damp cloth & let rise till doubled.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(400,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(400,3,'Punch down dough.  Divide into 3 & knead each piece for 3 minutes.  Shape into greased loaf tins, cover & let rise till doubled.  Bake at 350F for 1 hour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(400,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(400,5,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(401,1,'Wash & dice the potatoes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(401,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(401,3,'Put ghee in a pot, heat gently.  When hot, add the potatoes & cumin seeds. Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.  Add turmeric, ginger & peppers.  Cook, stirring, 3 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(401,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(401,5,'Add the remaining ingredients excepting the peas.  Lower the heat, cover & simmer for 15 minutes.  Check the water level, adding more if necessary.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(401,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(401,7,'Just prior to serving, add the peas.  Uncover, turn up the heat & cook til all the water has evaporated.');
