INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(539,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(539,5,'"Vegetarian Times" February, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(540,1,'Cream shortening & sugar for 30 seconds.  Beat in the vinegar.  Add flour, tartar, soda & salt.  Mix well.  Form into 1 inch balls & roll in the combined cinnamon-sugar mixture.  Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.  Bake at 350F for 10 minutes.  Cool on wire racks.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(540,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(540,3,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(541,1,'Boil the lentils for 5 minutes Empty the water and add 500ml of water Bring to the boil and allow to simmer for 10 minutes Add all the other ingredients and allow to cook on a low heat until all the ingredients are tender (takes about an hour or so)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(541,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(541,3,'Serve when thick');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(541,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(541,5,'Posted by Kaz Dunkley');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(542,1,'Soak the chickpeas for 24 hours, changing the water twice. Simmer for 30 minutes and then replace the water with hot water. Cook for 20 minutes, and change the water again. Keep the water level 5 cms above the chickpeas Add the rosemary, salt, pepper, and oil. Simmer until the chickpeas are tender. Add lemon juice to taste before serving');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(542,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(542,3,'Posted by Kaz Glover in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(543,1,'Cover the beans with water and bring to the boil.  Add all the ingredients, except the creamed coconut and stir.  Simmer for 45 minutes or until the beans are cooked and the liquid is reduced.  Stir in the creamed coconut and adjust the seasoning if necessary.  The stew should be hearty and thick.  Carrots or other vegetables can be added to the stew 10 minutes before it is done.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(543,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(543,3,'Note: Commercially-made, good quality creamed coconut can be bought in 7 ounce packets.  Available in most supermarkets, grocery and health shops, it can be stored for weeks in the refrigerator, to be used in sauces, stews, desserts and drinks.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(543,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(543,5,'Rosamund Grant, "Caribbean and African Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,1,'Combine TVP chunks, ketchup & water.  Soak for 5 minutes.  Add an additional cup of water & simmer on top of the stove for 20 minutes, till tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,3,'Combine vinegar, 1/2 c water, honey, bay leaf & cloves in a pan.  Bring to a boil & then add TVP.  Remove from heat & let marinate overnight in the refrigerator.  Remove TVP chunks & set aside.  Drain marinade, remove cloves.  Add cornstarch, soy sauce & sour cream to the marinade.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,5,'Heat oil in a skillet.  Add TVP chunks & cook till heated through.  Stir in marinade & cook for a few minutes more.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,7,'Serve over noodles.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(544,9,'"Vegetarian Times" February, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(545,1,'Cook soybeans in 3 cups water until tender, about 2 1/2 hours. Drain, cool and grind or blend to make 1 cup. Peel eggplant and cube. Combine with diced onion and 3 to 4 cloves garlic in saucepan and cook in enough oil to cover bottom of pan until onion is tender. Add oats, wheat germ, soybean mixture and salt. Stir in 2 tablespoons water. Dough should have consistency of thick paste. Press into patties and fry in 1/4 inch oil until done on both sides.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(545,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(545,3,'To make gravy, saute chopped onions, 2 cloves garlic and mushrooms in butter until mushrooms are tender. Dissolve arrowroot in 1/2 cup water and add to mushroom mixture. Cook and stir until thickened. Add tamari. Serve patties with gravy.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(545,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(545,5,'Created by: Golden Temple Conscious Cookery, Los Angeles');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(545,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(545,7,'(C) 1992 The Los Angeles Times');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(546,1,'Grind the almonds first in the blender dry.  Add the rest of the ingredients and in a blender until light and fluffy. Can be served cold or hot (do NOT boil!).  For variation sprinkle the top with some anise seed and/or coriander, or, orange or lemon rind gratings, or, powdered cardamom.  If your soy milk is not very sweet, then add a little honey to the above.  If you can''t find soy milk powder, then try thickening the soynog with, say, with 1/2 to one fresh banana.  If you want that slippery taste of "real" eggnog then just add more oil, but I think is better to simply allow your taste preferences to adapt and come to enjoy this soynog on its own terms   :-)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(546,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(546,3,'posted by Ted Wayn Altar in REC.FOOD.VEG');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(547,1,'Soak the soybeans and one piece of kombu in about five times their volume of water overnight.  Discard soaking water and kombu, rinse the beans and cook in about 4C water w/the other piece of kombu.  Cook until soft, about four hours, and drain.  Coarsely chop the beans and kombu, then mix in all remaining ingredients until you get a medium stiff mess. Pack the mix tightly into an oven safe glass or stainless steel bowl and cover tightly w/foil, carefully sealing the edges.  Invert a shallow, heat resistant bowl on the bottom of a large stock pot or dutch oven. Pour in enough water to cover the bowl, then place the soysage over the bowl.  Bring to a simmer, cover and steam about an hour and a half, checking occaionally to add water if needed.  Let cool and use.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(547,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(547,3,'Makes 3C');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(547,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(547,5,'This is from Brother Ron Pickarski''s great book _Friendly_Foods_, Berkeley, CA, Ten Speed Press 1991.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(547,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(547,7,'From: mad4@ellis.uchicago.edu (Bill Maddex)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(548,1,'In a medium sized bowl, mix tofu, nutritional yeast, oil & tamari.  Stir in the spaghetti & tomato sauce.  Heat through in a moderate oven till hot.  Serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(548,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(548,3,'"The Cookbook for People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(549,1,'Put oil in Dutch oven & saute onions & garlic till tender.  Add rest of the ingredients except the spaghetti.  Bring to a boil then reduce heat & simmer, stirring occasionally.  Cook for 1 hour.  Serve over spaghetti.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(549,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(549,3,'"Vegetarian Times Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,1,'In a large saucepan place the oil and heat it on medium high until it is hot.  Add the parsley, onions, and garlic.  Saute the ingredients for 3 to 4 minutes, or until the onions are translucent.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,3,'Add the water and bring it to a boil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,5,'Add the tomato paste, chopped tomatoes, salt, and pepper.  Mix the ingredients together thoroughly so that everything is well combined.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,7,'Add the spinach and rice.  Simmer the ingredients for 30 minutes on low heat, or until the rice is done.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(550,9,'Source: Papadakis Taverna - San Pedro, California California Beach Recipe - by Joan & Carl Stromquist - ISBN: 0-9622807-3-9 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,1,'Start by making the pastry.  Sift the flour with the salt and baking powder. Mix in about 6 tablespoons water, a little at a time, until the dough is gooey, but not wet.  Add 1 tablespoon olive oil, plus another teaspoonful, and a little more flour, if needed, to make a cohesive mass. Knead the dough for 5 to 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic.  Cover it and set aside to relax for an hour or two.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,3,'For the filling, separate the curly endive leaves, so the vegetable will cook in the same time.  Steam the spinach and endive together in a large pan, in the water clinging to the leaves, plus just an extra 1/2 cup. Turn the leaves over occasionally, so they wilt evenly.  When they are wilted, but not mushy, drain them in a colander, pressing firmly with the back of a wooden spoon to remove as much excess liquid as possible. (Reserve the liquid for use in soup, or drink with a squeeze of lemon juice, as the Greeks do.)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,5,'Saute the scallions in 2 tablespoons olive oil, until barely soft.  Add a few tablespoons of water if they stick to the pan.  Roughly chop the cooked spinach and curly endive and finely grate the zest from the lemon. Then toss the cooked vegetables with the scallions, parsley, dill, lemon zest and 1 tablespoon lemon juice, salt, and pepper, adding 3 tablespoons olive oil. Set aside until you are ready to fill the pastry.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,7,'Choose an ovenproof earthenware or glass baking dish 2 to 2-1/2 inches deep and about 2-quart capacity and brush the inside with oil.  Divide the pastry into two unequal parts, and then again into halves.  On a floured surface roll out one of the larger pieces of pastry. This should be large enough to line the dish, coming up and over the sides - this should make it very thin.  Fit it into the baking dish and brush it with olive oil. Do the same with the second piece of pastry, placing it on top of the first, and brush again with olive oil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,9,'Sprinkle the tablespoon of rice or cracked wheat over the bottom, to soak up excess juices, and fill with the spinach and herb mixture.  Roll out the remaining two pieces of pastry, separately, to fit the top of the dish.  Place the first on top of the spinach, brush with olive oil, then place the second on top of that.  Prick the pastry with a fork in an attractive pattern and brush the entire top with olive oil.  Sprinkle with sesame seeds.  Bake in an oven preheated to 350 F for 45-50 minutes, until golden brown.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,11,'                Source: Recipes from a Greek Island - by Susie Jacobs');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,12,'                ISBN: 0-671-74531-X');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(551,13,'                Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,1,'SERVES: 6-8 OVEN TEMPERATURE: 180øC (350øF) COOKING TIME: 50 Minutes');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,3,'Wash spinach well and cut off any coarse stems.  Chop coarsely and put into a large pan.  Cover and place over heat for 7-8 minutes shaking pan now and then or turning spinach with a fork.  Heat just long enough to wilt spinach so that juices can run out freely.  Drain well in colander, pressing occasionally with a spoon.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,5,'Gently fry onion in olive oil for 10 minutes, add chopped leek and spring onions and fry gently for further 5 minutes until transparent.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,7,'Place well-drained spinach in a mixing bowl and add oil and onion mixture, herbs and nutmeg.  Blend thoroughly, adding salt and pepper to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,9,'Place a sheet of fillo pastry on work surface and brush lightly with olive oil.  Top with 3 more sheets of pasry, brushing each with oil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,11,'Brush top layer lightly with oil and place half the spinach mixture along the length of the pastry towards one edge and leaving 4 cm (1-1/2 inches) clear on each side.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,13,'Fold bottom edge of pastry over filling, roll once, fold in sides then roll up.  Place a hand at each end of roll and push it in gently like a concertina.  Repeat with remaining pastry and filling.  Place rolls in an oiled baking dish leaving space between rolls.  Brush tops lightly with oil and bake in a moderate oven for 30 minutes until golden. Serve hot cut in portions.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,15,'                Source: The Complete Middle East Cookbook - by Tess Mallos');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,16,'                ISBN: 1 86302 069 1');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(552,17,'                Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(553,1,'COOK THE RICE according to the instructions on the package and keep warm. Heat the oil over medium heat in a large skillet and add the onions. Cook, stirring, about 5 minutes. Add the garlic and cook another minute. Add the peppers and tomatoes, cover and cook about 5 minutes. Add the rice, mix, replace the cover and cook another minute or so. Taste for salt and pepper and serve immediately.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(553,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(553,3,'Michael Roberts, "Prodigy Guest Chefs Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(554,1,'Saute mushrooms in 2 tb margarine for a few minutes.  Add salt & pepper. Cover & remove from heat.  Saute the onion & garlic in the oil & remaining margarine.  Raise heat a little & add the rice, stirring till well coated. Add green pepper, tomatoes, hot water, cloves, bay leaf, cayenne, mushrooms & stir.  Cover, reduce heat & simmer for 15 minutes.  Add wine after about 10 minutes.  Remove cloves & bay leaf & sprinkle with parsley before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(554,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(554,3,'Vera Gewanter, "A Passion for Vegetables"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(555,1,'In a heavy skillet, heat oil & saute onions.  Add other ingredients, stirring well so that they are coated with theo il.  Cover & simmer for 15 minutes or till the peppers are cooked but firm.  Add water if the casserole is too dry.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(555,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(555,3,'Vera Gewanter "A Passion for Vegetables"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(556,1,'Heat oil & saute onions for a few minutes.  Add remaining ingredients & a little water.  Cover & simmer for 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(556,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(556,3,'Vera Gewanter, "A Passion for Vegetables"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(557,1,'Beat shortening for 30 seconds.  Add sugar & beat till ight & fluffy & well combined.  Add the dry ingredients alternately with the water, a little at a time, beating well after each addition.  Finally mix in the raisins.  Bake in a large greased loaf pan for 45 minutes at 325F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(557,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(557,3,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(558,1,'Beat shortening for 30 seconds.  Add sugar & beat till well blended.  Add molasses & beat again for a few seconds.  Stir in the dry ingredients & spices in order, ensuring that they are well blended after each addition. Add flour a little at a time.  Mix thoroughly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(558,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(558,3,'Roll out dough till paper thin, you can do this in several batches.  Cut with cookie cutters & place on greased cookie sheets.  Bake for 5 to 6 minutes at 375F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(558,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(558,5,'Makes 60.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(558,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(558,7,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(559,1,'Pre-heat oven to 400F.  Wash & scrub potatoes, leaving the skins on.  Cut the into sticks & set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(559,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(559,3,'Mix together spices & oil.  Add potato sticks to mixture & coat well.  Lay onto a cookie sheet & bake for 30 to 40 minutes.  Stir them half way through cooking.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(559,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(559,5,'"Vegetarian Times" October, 1991');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,1,'Drain beans.  Cover with fresh water, bring to a boil & boil fast for 10 minutes.  Reduce heat & simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.  Drain, reserving the stock.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,3,'Meanwhile, fry the onion & garlic in olive oil for 3 to 4 minutes.  Put in the spices & for another 2 minutes, stirring.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,5,'Add the drained beans, bell peppers, carrots, peanuts & sliced orange. Cook covered over a gentle heat for 10 minutes.  Stir occasionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,7,'Mix in sherry, lemon juice & shoyu.   Add about 2 tb of reserved stock, but not too much as the curry should be dry not wet.  Cook, covered, for another 10 to 15 minutes.  Serve, garnished with extra orange slices.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(560,9,'Sarah Brown''s "Vegetarian Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(561,1,'After soaking, drain the chick peas.  Cook in fresh water for 60 minutes till tender, drain & reserve liquid.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(561,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(561,3,'Heat oil in large skillet.  Fry gently the onion together with the spices for 5 to 7 minutes.  Add the bell peppers & chick peas.  Dissolve tomato paste into the stock & add to the skillet.  Cook for 10 minutes.  aste for seasonings.  Add lemon juice & salt & pepper.  Serve over rice or pasta.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(561,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(561,5,'Sarah Brown, "Vegetarian Kitchen"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(562,1,'Mix cumin, turmeric, chili powder, salt & lemon juice in a small bowl. Add mustard & mix into a wet paste.  Cut stems off okra then split them three quarters of the way down.  Split them again, dividing pods into 4 equal parts that are held together at the narrow end tip.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(562,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(562,3,'Pour al ittle of the paste in to the openings, spread it lightly all over but the narrow tip.  Sprinkle with salt.  Heat oil in a skillet & fry okra, covered, till tender, about 10 minutes, turning them once.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(562,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(562,5,'Ismail Merchant, "Indian Cuisine"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(563,1,'Dice the carrots.  Melt the margarine in a small pot, add carrots & cook over a gentle heat for 5 minutes.  Pour in the cider & water.  Add the rosemary & mustard.  Bring to a boil & simmer covered for 10 minutes.  Add more liquid if necessary.  When the carrots are tender, put them in a warmed serving dish & continue to cook the sauce till it is thickened & syrupy.  Pour over the carrots & serve straight away.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(563,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(563,3,'Sarah Brown "Vegetarian Kitchen"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(564,1,'Wash & scrub potatoes.  Cut into sticks & set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(564,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(564,3,'Mix together oil & spices.  Dip the potatoes into the mixture & spread onto a cookie sheet.  Bake at 400F for 30 to 40 minutes, stirring half way through cooking.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(564,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(564,5,'"Vegetarian Times" October, 1991');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(565,1,'Depending on the size of the potatoes, either leave them whole or quarter them, but do not cut them too small.  Chop the broccoli, reserving the inner stem, but discarding the fibrous outside.  Chop the head.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(565,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(565,3,'Over boiling water, steam the potatoes, broccoli stem, carrots & cauliflower.  After 10 minutes, add broccoli heads & steam until vegetables are just tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(565,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(565,5,'In a heavy pot, saute the onions in the ghee till they are transparent. Mix in all the steamed vegetables except the broccoli.  Cover & cook for 6 to 8 minutes, stirring often.  Add broccoli & cook for another 5 minutes. Serve with bread.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(565,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(565,7,'"The Africa News Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(566,1,'Put legumes in separate bowls.  Whisk together mustard, garlic, parsley, vinegar, lemon juice, salt, oil & red pepper.  Divide mixture evenly between legumes.  Marinate covered in the fridge for 1 hour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(566,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(566,3,'Line salad plates with lettuce, top with peppers.  Arrange small piles of potatoes, carrots & legumes on each plate.  Drizzle marinade over the meal.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(566,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(566,5,'"Vegetarian Times" July, 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(567,1,'  300 cc Water, 40øC');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(567,2,'   10 g  Herbs of Provence');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(567,3,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(567,4,'Give the flour in a pot, mix well with herbes, add salt and yeast at different ends of the pot, add water while stirring, add leaven. Knead well during 5 min. Cover and let rest for 30 min. Knead well and form as you like. Cover and let rest 60 min. til it doubled its volume. Bake in preheated oven at 225øC for 70 min. You can use single herbs (e.g. thyme) instead of h. of Provence. If you divide the paste in two parts the baking time would be 50 min.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(567,5,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(567,6,'Source Unknown');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(568,1,'Heat ghee in a large casserole.  When hot, toss in the ginger, chilies, mustard & cumin seeds.  Fry till the mustard seeds start to pop.  Stir in the cauliflower, coriander, turmeric & salt.  Stir fry for a couple of minutes, till the cauliflower starts to turn brown.  Then add the tomatoes.  Cover, reduce heat to low.  Cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(568,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(568,3,'Remove the lid & stir fry for a few minutes till the liquid has evaporated.  Sprinkle with garam masala & coriander greens & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(568,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(568,5,'Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking".');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(569,1,'Place bulgur in a heat-proof serving dish.  Pour on boiling water & let stand while preparing the other ingredients.  Mix together miso, water, honey & sesame oil.  Set aside.  Heat oil in a wok & saute eggplant for 5 minutes, stirring.  Add garlic & ginger & saute for 2 minutes.  Add tofu & saute for 5 minutes.  Add miso mixture & stir fry for 4 minutes.  Add onions & pepper flakes & cook till tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(569,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(569,3,'Pour off any excess water from the bulgur.  Fluff with a fork & top with eggplant.  Serve immediately.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(569,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(569,5,'"Vegetarian Times Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,1,'Put the tamarind in a nonmetallic bowl.  Add 1/4 cup boiling water and let it soak for 30 minutes.  Mash the pulp and extract as much juice from it as possible.  Pour all liquid into a bowl, and save the fibrous residue for making the sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,3,'Slit the eggplants lengthwise to within 3/4 inch of the stem end so that each eggplant remains in one piece.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,5,'Measure out the spices and place them right next to the stove in separate piles.  Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a large frying pan or skillet over medium-high heat for 1 minute.  Add the garlic and fry for 30 seconds.  Add the coriander, cinnamon, and cloves; fry for 15 more seconds.  Stir in the coconut and cayenne pepper; continue frying, stirring, until lightly toasted (about 2 minutes).  Turn off the heat and stir in the salt, tamarind liquid, and molasses, and mix well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,7,'Stuff the eggplants with the spicy coconut mixture.  Secure them by wrapping thread around them.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,9,'Heat the remaining 1 tablespoon oil in the same pan over medium-high heat. When it is hot, add mustard seeds.  Keep a pot lid handy, as the seeds may spatter and fly all over.  When the seeds stop spattering, add the eggplants in one layer.  Fry the eggplants, turning them often, for 3 or 4 minutes.  Reduce heat to medium or medium low and cook them, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes or until they are soft and cooked through.  Turn off heat.  Transfer them to a serving platter, pour Ginger-Tamarind sauce over them, and serve immediately.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,11,'GINGER-TAMARIND SAUCE: Put tamarind residue in a nonmetallic bowl, add 1/2 cup boiling water, and let soak for 30 minutes.  Mash the residue and extract as much tamarind essence as possible, squeezing it hard, into a bowl.  Discard the fibrous residue.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,13,'Put tamarind water in a nonmetallic pan along with cornstarch, mix well and bring to a boil.  Cook for 2 minutes.  Turn off heat and stir in ginger shreds.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,15,'Note: For a hotter flavor, stir 4 chopped hot green chilies into sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,16,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(570,17,'Source: Classic Indian Vegetarian and Grain Cooking, by Julie Sahni Typos by: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(571,1,'[Asian accents make this a perfect partner for Japanese noodles, such as udon (use about 12 ounces, dry weight).  Serve the finished pasta well chilled.]');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(571,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(571,3,'Whisk all ingredients to blend in large bowl.  Refrigerate.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(571,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(571,5,'Source: Richard Sax and Marie Simmons - Bon Appetit, September 1991 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,1,'Mix sauce ingredients together in a small bowl.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,3,'Heat oil in a nonstick pan or wok; brown ginger root.  Add tofu and 1 tablespoon soy sauce; stir gently and occasionally for 2 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,5,'Add chopped mushrooms and water chestnuts; stir gently for 2 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,7,'Add minced green onions and sauce mixture and stir for 1 minute.  Serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,9,'Per serving: Calories: 153                   Fat: 11 gm (saturated fat = 8%) Carbohydrates: 8 gm             Cholesterol: 0 mg Protein: 8 gm                   Sodium: 237 mg Fiber: 2 gm                     Calcium: 95 mg');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(572,11,'Source: Nutritional Cooking with Tofu, by Christine Y.C. Liu, M.P.H. Typos by: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,1,'Rinse & cook lentils.  when done, drain & set aside.  Reserve stock for later in the recipe.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,3,'Saute onions & garlic in the ghee till onions are just translucent.  Add berbere, cumin & paprika.  Saute for a few minutes longer, stirring occasionally to prevent anything from burning.  Mix in tomatoes & tomato paste.  Simmer 10 minutes.  Add stock & continue simmering.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,5,'When lentils are cooked, mix them into the saute.  Add green peas & cook another 5 minutes.  Add salt & pepper to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,7,'Serve with Injera bread or pita bread.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(573,9,'"Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(574,1,'Saute onions, garlic, berbere & paprika in ghee for 2 minutes.  Add beans, carrots & potatoes.  Saute for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally to prevent burning.  Add tomatoes, tomato paste & stock.  Bring to a boil, cover & simmer for 15 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(574,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(574,3,'Add salt & pepper to taste & mix in the parsley.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(574,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(574,5,'"Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(575,1,'Boil spinach & turnips in water for 12 to 15 minutes.  remove & set in a bowl.  Mash with a fork.  Rinse the pot & heat the ghee.  Add mustard seeds & a few seconds later add the onion, garlic & ginger.  Cook til lthe onion is browned.  Add turmeric, chili, garam masala & salt.  Stir in the mashed vegetables.  Cover & simmer for 5 minutes until all the liquid has evaporated, stirring occasionally.  Serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(575,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(575,3,'Rani, "Feast of India"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(576,1,'Heat oil in large pot over medium low heat.  Add onion & cook till it turns brown, stirring occasionally.  Stir in potatoes & cook till they begin to brown.  Stir frequently.  Add cayenne, lemon, salt & turmeric. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.  Add cauliflower & chilies & stir well.  Add about 1/4 c water.  Continue to cook till the vegetables are tender, adding more water if necessary.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(576,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(576,3,'Adapted from Ismail Merchant, "Indian Cuisine"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(577,1,'Drain & rinse tofu.  Drain again.  Cut into 1 inch square pieces.  Set wok over high flame & add oil.  When hot, add ginger, garlic & 2 tb scallions, cook for 30 seconds.  Add hot bean paste & tofu.  Stir gently.  Add tamari, salt, sugar & stock, bring to a full boil.  Thicken with cornstarch.  Add sesame oil, chili oil & peppercorn powder.  Sprinkle with remaining scallions & serve with brown rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(577,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(577,3,'"Vegetarian Times Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(578,1,'Mash tofu in a large bowl. Add remaining ingredients, mix well with fork or by hand. Pack into small oiled casserole dish; cover with two or three paper towels. Steam 25 to 35 minutes on a rack inside a covered pot with water on stove or in a pan of water in the oven at 375 degrees. Top will brown slightly. Cool before removing from dish. Steaming blends flavors. Stores up to two weeks in fridge. Makes 2.5 cups.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(578,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(578,3,'JTK''s notes: I accidently used wheat bran instead of germ, and it still worked (kind of dry, though). I made this in a 2-qt. porcelain souffle dish, which it filled approx. 2/3.  I didn''t have savory so I substituted fresh thyme. As usual, I added more garlic & hot sauce. Mash tofu very well, or you will have lots of tofu lumps --- I think I might try blending this in the food processor next time, to avoid this problem.  This was enough for maybe 4 days of lunches for me (pate on 4-5 Wasa breads/rice cakes per day).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(578,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(578,5,'(vegan) --- from the net, don''t know authorship (sorry).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(579,1,'Heat a wok or heavy soup pot on high heat for 30 seconds.  Add the oil & swirl to coat.  Add garlic, leeks, carrots & lower to a simmer & cook, covered for 10 minutes.  Stir occasionally.  Uncover wok, increase heat to high & add spinach & water chestnuts.  Stir-fry for 2 minutes.  Lower heat to medium.  Add warmed stock, tamari & rice vinegar.  Season to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(579,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(579,3,'Heat through but do not boil.  Serve immediately, garnished with tofu strips.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(579,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(579,5,'"Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(580,1,'Chop the washed spinach.  Boil lentils in 4 cups water with bay leaves until they are soft.  Heat oil in a pot & gently fry the green onions for 2 minutes.  Add garlic & seasonings.  Add spinach.  Mix well & put in cooked lentils.  Add another pint of water or stock & cook for a further 15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(580,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(580,3,'Jack Santa Maria, "Greek Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,1,'Boil spinach & potatoes.  Drain, peel potatoes & grind with the spinach. Add chick pea flour & blend.  Stir on milk or cream.  Add salt, turmeric, garam masala, mango powder (omit if you want) & cayenne.  Mix together till you have a smooth dough.  pluck off small pieces & shape into a ball or any other shape you might desire.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,3,'Heat sufficient ghee in a wok or deep skillet.  Roll each ball in coconut & deep fry till completely golden.  Remove & place on a plate.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,5,'Heast gravy in a pot over medium heat.  Drop in the koftas, cover, lower heat & cook for 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,7,'Garnish with coriander & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(581,9,'Michael Pandya, "Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,1,'This dish, traditionally made with mixed greens such as spinach and mustard, resembles an Italian pesto, though it is much thicker in consistency.  In place of olive oil, mustard oil is used, and apart from the taste of the greens themselves, the other strong flavors include raw garlic, raw ginger, green chilis, and cilantro.  If you can''t obtain the pungent golden mustard oil which is called for in this recipe (available in Chinese as well as Indian groceries), steep 1/2 teaspoon powdered dried mustard in 2 tablespoons of vegetable oil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,3,'In Northern India, this dish is eaten at room temperature for breakfast, along with fried bread and tea.  While raw garlic may seem alarming first thing in the morning, Indians consider it a medicinal necessity, and many swallow a crushed clove every day.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,5,'DIRECTIONS: ========== Bring 4 quarts of water to a rolling boil in a large pot.  Add spinach and cook on high heat for 1 to 2 minutes, or until wilted.  Drain, rinse under cold water, and squeeze out as much liquid as you can easily.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,7,'Put spinach in food processor or blender with 2 tablespoons water and blend until smooth.  This will result in a fairly thick paste.  Put in a serving bowl.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,9,'Whisk together ginger, garlic, green chili, salt, cilantro, and oil.  Pour this dressing over the spinach and mix thoroughly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(582,11,'Source: (C) 1981 Madhur Jaffrey The Herb Companion - February/March 1993 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,1,'Blend tofu in processor.  Add salt, lemon juice, vegetable oil, tahini & miso.  Blend till thoroughly smooth.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,3,'Heat olive oil.  Add onion & saute till translucent.  Add garlic, pepper, nutmeg, tarragon, dill & mushrooms.  Saute for several minutes.  Stir in chopped spinach & parsley.  Saute very briefly.  Remove from heat.  Add the saute to tofu mixture.  Blend briefly.  Be sure to maintain the texture.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,5,'Pre-heat oven to 350F.  Lightly oil the bottom & sides of a baking dish. Add 2 to 3 tb of breadcrumbs & ensure that the dish is evenly coated. Sprinkle 1/3 of walnuts on bottom of dish, followed by 1/4 of the tomato sauce.  Lay 3 noodles on top of the sauce & evenly spread half the tofu mixture on the noodles.  Repeat a second layer.  Then top with remaining walnuts, noodles & sauce. Sprinkle the rest of the breadcrumbs on top,');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,7,'Cover & bake for 30 minutes.  Uncover & bake another 10 minutes.  Cool for 20 to 30 minutes before slicing.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(583,9,'Source Unknown');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(584,1,'DOUGH:  In a large bowl, mix together yeast, water & sugar.  Let stand for 5 minutes.  Add oil, flour & salt.  Knead about 5 minutes into a smooth, elastic ball of dough.  Cover & let rise till doubled in size. Punch down. Roll out 2/3 of the dough into a 12 inch circle & fit it into a 10 inch springform pan, patting it up the sides. Set aside.  Reserve the remaining dough.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(584,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(584,3,'FILING:  Mix together the TVP, boiling water, oregano, basil & fennel.  In a large skillet, heat olive oil.  Saute TVP mixture for a few minutes. Stir in mushrooms, spinach, tomato paste & water.  Heat through.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(584,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(584,5,'Prejeat oven to 375F.  Spread filling onto the dough.  Roll remaining dough into a 10 inch circle & cut into 8 wedges.  Arrange the wedges on top of the filling, overlapping slightly, sealing the wide ends to the bottom crust.  Brush the top with a little soymilk.  Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(584,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(584,7,'"Vegetarian Times" February, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(585,1,'Cook the spinach without added water in a covered pot fro just a few minutes - until tender & very bright green.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(585,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(585,3,'Transfer to a blender & with 1/4 cup water, puree till very smooth.  Place in a small bowl.  Thin to desired consistency & season with garlic, salt & pepper.  Serve on cold pasta or on hot baked potatoes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(585,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(585,5,'"Vegetarian Times" April, 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(586,1,'Place spinach in a large salad bowl.  Add orange, mushrooms & onions.  Mix together lemon juice, oil, garlic powder, salt & pepper.  Ensure it is well mixed.  Pour over salad & add almonds.  Toss gently.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(586,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(586,3,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(587,1,'Steep split peas in hot water for an hour then drain.  Fry onion & garlic in soup pot for 4 minutes.  Add the rest of the vegetables plus the peas, the caraway seed, the bay leaf & the mace.  Cook for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring occasionally.  Add most of the stock.  Bring to a boil, reduce heat & simmer for 40 minutes.  Remove the bay leaf & allow to cool slightly.  Blend till smooth.  Reheat before serving, but don''t boil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(587,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(587,3,'Sarah Brown''s "Vegetarian Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(588,1,'Wash lentils.  Put in a large pot with turmeric & 4 cups of water.  Bring to a boil, reduce heat & simmer, partially covered, for 30 minutes.  Add another 3/4 cups water & continue to simmer for another 30 minutes.  Stir often to prevent burning.  You should have a stiff puree.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(588,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(588,3,'While lentils are cooking, wash vegetables & dry.  Prepare sprouts as you would for any cooking.  Heat oil in a deep saucepan & when very hot, add mustard seeds.  After 15 seconds, add fenugreek.  Then add garlic & sambaar powder.  Stir for a moment & add sprouts & beans.  Fry the vegetables, turning & tossing them for 2 to 3 minutes.  Add tamarind paste, salt & 1/4 cup warm water.  Reduce heat & cook, covered, for 20 minutes.  Add lentils to the vegetables.  Cook for another 10 to 15 minutes, or until the vegetables are completely cooked. Stir in coriander & serve with plain cooked rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(588,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(588,5,'Julie Sahni, "Classic Indian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(589,1,'Heat oil in a skillet, add onion & bay leaves & cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.  Meanwhile, peel the eggplant, slice it then dice. Add pieces to skillet.  Add rest of the ingredients.  Raise heat till mixture begins to simmer then cover, reduce heat & simmer 20 minutes til the eggplant is very tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(589,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(589,3,'Ismail Merchant, "Indian Cuisine"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(590,1,'SAUCE:  Mash together the beans, garlic & ginger root in a mortar & pestle.  Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(590,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(590,3,'STIR FRY:  In a wok, heat sherry/stock to simmering.  Add onion & stir for 3 minutes.  Add garlic, bok choy, pepper & cabbage.  Cover & steam for 5 minutes.  Add honey, tamari & dissolved cornstarch.  Cook & stir till sauce thickens slightly.  Remove from heat & stir in 1 tb black bean sauce. Serve over rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(590,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(590,5,'"Vegetarian Times" September, 1990');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(591,1,'Heat oil in wok.  When hot, add bell peppers, celery & garlic.  Stir fry over moderate heat till celery is half cooked.  Add bean sprouts, scallions & sunflower seeds.  Stir fry just till sprouts are wilted.  Rest of the vegetables should be tender crisp.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(591,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(591,3,'Add rest of ingredients & reduce heat.  Saute another 2 minutes.  Serve over grains or noodles.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(591,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(591,5,'Nava Atlas, "Vegetariana"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(592,1,'Trim the green beans and cut each one in half.  Boil them in ample water for 2 minutes and drain well.  Cut the bean curd into 3/4-inch cubes. Crush and chop the garlic.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(592,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(592,3,'Heat the oil in a frying pan or wok.  When hot, add the garlic, salt, and green beans.  Stir-fry over medium heat for 2-1/2 minutes.  Add the bean curd pieces and turn them lightly with the beans for 1-1/2 minutes.  Pour in all the sauce ingredients.  Turn and stir them together for 1 minute. Cook and turn for 1-1/2 minutes and serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(592,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(592,5,'Serves 4-5 with rice and other dishes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(592,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(592,7,'Source: New Chinese Vegetarian Cooking, by Kenneth Lo Typos by: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(593,1,'Wash, hull & half the strawberries.  Peel, core & quarter the apples.  Ten cut quarters into thin slices.  Put all the ingredients, except the sugar, into a large pot.  Cover & bring to a boil.  Simmer until the fruit is tender.  Add warmed sugar & stir till it has dissolved.  Increase heat, stirring frequently & cook till setting point is reached.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(593,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(593,3,'Remove from heat & let stand for 5 minutes.  Pour into warm sterile jars & seal.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(593,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(593,5,'Letts, "Jams, Pickles & Chutneys"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(594,1,'Wash & drain fruit, then remove stalks.  Cover friuit with 1/2 cup of sugar & stand overnight.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(594,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(594,3,'Strain liquid from strawberries.  Place in pot, add remaining sugar & stir over low heat for 10 minutes.  Do not allow to boil.  Add fruit & cook till setting point is reached, about 20 to 30 minutes.  Ladle into warm sterile jars.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(594,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(594,5,'Letts "Jams, Pickles & Chutneys"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(595,1,'Mix together fruit & sugar & let stand for one hour.  Boil water & certo crystals hard one minute.  Add fruit & place in jars.  Refrigerate.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(595,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(595,3,'"Our Best to you Recipes"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(596,1,'Thaw & mash strawberries.  Add white sugar.  Boil for 8 minutes in a laege pot.  Remove from stove & let cool.  Stir & skim off any foam.  Bottle in sterilized jars.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(596,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(596,3,'"Our Best to You Recipes"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(597,1,'Wash & hull the berries.  Place in a large pot.  Cover with boiling water & let stand for 3 minutes.  Drain.  Add 2 1/2 cups of water, boil hard for 3 minutes.  Add remaining sugar & boil hard for another 3 minutes.  Let stand overnight, either in large bowls or platters.  Ladle into serile jars.  Seal.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(597,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(597,3,'"From Our Parish Kitchens Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(598,1,'Wash & hull strawberries.  Peel, core & finely chop apple.  Add lime juice & let stand covered for 30 minutes.  Microwave the fruit & juice for 4 minutes on high.  Add sugar, stir & microwave 35 minutes on high, stirring every 10 minutes.  Stand five minutes, pour into warm sterile jars.  Seal.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(598,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(598,3,'Letts, "Jams, Pickles & Chutneys"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,1,'Preheat oven to 400F/200C.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,3,'Slice eggplants in half & rub oil lightly over the skin.  Place face down on a greased tray & bake 1 hour.  Leave to cool.  Scoop out the insides & blend with the almonds, onion, garlic & parsley.  Season well & chill thoroughly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,5,'Cut cumcumber into 8 x 1 inch rounds.  Scoop out the middle of each round to form a small case, be careful not to cut all the way through.  Either leave the cases raw or blanch in boiling water for 5 minutes.  Fill cucumber chunks with the eggplant pate.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,7,'Line a serving platter with lettuce & edge this with tomato slices.  Put cucumber cases in the centre & garnish with lemon & parsley.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(599,9,'Sarah Brown, "Vegetarian Kitchen"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(600,1,'Cut eggplants in half & scoop out pulp.  Leave 1/2" skin.  Place shells in shallow baking dish.  Dice pulp.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(600,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(600,3,'Saute onions in oil till tender, don''t brown.  Add cubed eggplant pulp & cook till tender.  Add garlic, mushrooms & bulgur.  Cook for 3 minutes, stirring often.  Add stock & rest of the ingredients.  Bring to a boil, cover & simmer for 20 minutes or till moisture is absorbed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(600,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(600,5,'Spoon into prepared shells.  Drizzle a little more olive oil over the top if desired & pour 1/2 c water into baking dish.  Bake at 350F for 40 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(600,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(600,7,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(601,1,'Wash peppers & cut off & retain the tops.  Remove seed & pulp & discard. Heat oil in a pan & gently fry the onion for 2 minutes.  Sprinkle on the herbs & salt & pepper.  Add tomatoes & fry together for 2 minutes.  Add cooked rice & nuts & fry together for 2 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(601,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(601,3,'Fill each pepper with the cooked filling.  Place on a baking sheet & put on the caps.  Pour a little oil on each & bake at 375F until the peppers are browned.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(601,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(601,5,'Jack Santa Maria, "Greek Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(602,1,'In a skillet, heat oil and saute onion and mushrooms until soft. Add parsley and spices. Tranfer to a bowl. Mix in peas and rice. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line a 3-quart baking dish with a few grape leaves to keep stuffed leaves from sticking and burning. Place 1 heaping tablespoon of rice mixture (more or less depending on size of leaf) in the center of a grape leaf. Fold in sides, then roll leaf from stem to tip. Place in casserole. Repeat procedure with remaining grape leaves until rice mixture is used up. Pour water in bottom of dish (to prevent sticking and drying out). Bake for 25 minutes. Serves 12 as an appetizer, 6 as an entree. Per appetizer serving: 91 cal.; 3g prot.; 2.5g fat; 14g carb.; 0 chol.; 94mg sod. From _Vegetarian Times_, March 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,1,'In a medium saucepan place the water and bring it to a boil.  Remove the pan from the heat and add the grape leaves.  Let the grape leaves sit in the hot water for 10 minutes.  Remove them from the water and set them aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,3,'In a medium bowl, place the cooked rice, onions, parsley, tomatoes, dried mint, allspice, and garlic.  Mix the ingredients together well.  Let the mixture sit for 2 hours.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,5,'In the center of each grape leaf place a small amount of the rice mixture. Fold the bottom of the grape leaf up and the sides over.  Roll the grape leaf up.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,7,'Line the bottom of a large saucepan with some of the grape leaves.  Place the rolled grape leaves on top, seam side down, so that they are tightly packed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,9,'Sprinkle on the lemon juice.  Add enough water to cover the rolled grape leaves.  Place an oven-proof plate on top of the rolled grape leaves to press them down.  Cover the pot and bring the liquid to a boil over high heat.  Reduce the heat to low and simmer the rolled grape leaves for 45 to 60 minutes, or until most of the water is absorbed.  Let them sit for 1 hour before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(603,11,'Source: Papa Garo''s - Redondo Beach, California "Southern California Beach Recipe" by Joan and Carl Stromquist ISBN: 0-9622807-3-9 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(604,1,'Pre-heat oven to 350F.  Wipe mushrooms clean.  Remove stems & save for another use.  Lightly oil baking sheet with 2 tb oil & lay mushrooms on it stalk side up.  Pour 1/2 ts olive oil over each one & bake for 20 minutes.  Remove from oven & set aside to cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(604,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(604,3,'Combine tomatoes, garlic & scallions on a chopping board & chop unil reduced to a puree.  Put in a bowl & stir on the chives & salt & pepper. Stir in the rest of the oilve oil & lemon juice.  Fill each mushroom cap & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(604,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(604,5,'"Vegetarian Times" December, 1991');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,1,'1.  Preheat the oven to 350 F.  Gently clean the mushrooms with a damp cloth.  Remove the stems and chop them finely.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,3,'2.  Heat the oil (or water) in a skillet.  Add the onion and cook until golden.  Add the garlic and cook 1 minute more. Add the chopped mushroom stems, basil, oregano, and parsley, and cook 5 minutes, stirring, occasionally.  Add the bread crumbs, petter, soy sauce, and sherry, and heat, stirring for 2 minutes. Add additional salt and pepper if needed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,5,'3.  Place the mushroom caps, open side up, in a lightly oiled baking dish. Fill each cap with the bread crumb mixture, forming a mound with your fingers.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,7,'4.  Bake for 15 minutes and serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,9,'"The High Road to Health" by Lindsey Wagner and Ariane Spade.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(605,11,'FROM:    LISA DEBOVSKI   (NDTK86B)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,1,'Slice the stems off the okra & the very tip at the other end.  Slit each pod lengthwise, leaving 1/4-inch unslit at both ends.  Be careful not to cut the pods completely in half.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,3,'Combine the crushed coriander, cumin & fennel seeds with the balck pepper, garam masala, cayenne, asafetida, almonds, lemon juice & 2 tb of ghee. Blend well, using your fingers if necessary till you have a dry oatmeal type texture.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,5,'Using a butter knife, put about a 1/4 ts of the stuffing into each okra pod, then press the edges closed & set aside covered till you are ready to cook.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,7,'Place the rest of the ghee in a large skillet & heat till hot.  Add the stuffed okra pods & spread out in one layer.  Keeping the heat moderate, cook for 5 minutes, covered.  Gently turn the okra to ensure even cooking. Continue this for 20 to 25 minutes or until the okra is completely cooked.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,9,'Place the okra on paper towels & toss with salt.  Serve piping hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(606,11,'Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(607,1,'Steam the zucchini for 5 minutes; cut in half and scoop out seeds. Cube the tofu and marinate for 2 hours in the soy sauce and peanut butter. Fry in 2 T oil until browned. Add 2 T oil to another pan and saute the onions, celery, mushrooms, the chopped zucchini pulp, and 1 clove garlic. Add the bread crumbs and marinated tofu and stuff mixture into zucchini shells. Simmer the remaining ingredients and 4 cups water for 10 minutes and pour over zucchini shells.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(607,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(607,3,'Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(607,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(607,5,'From _Favorite Vegetarian Recipes_, from the Society for Texas Animal Rights');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(607,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(607,7,'DEEANNE [EatMoVeggies]       at 19:13 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(608,1,'Rinse peas and lentils.  Soak beans in 6 cups water up to 8 hours. Using the same soaking water, bring the beans to a boil and skim off any foam that accumulates.  Add caraway, onion, celery, carrots.  Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 40 minutes.  Add the sunchokes, and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer an additional 10 minutes until sunchokes are crisp-tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(608,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(608,3,'Nutritional Information Per Serving:  Protein - 14 grams (25%); Carbohydrates - 39.5 grams (72%); Fat - .5 grams (3%); Calories - 212; Sodium - 213 mg.; Cholesterol - 0 mg.  Exchanges: 2 starch/bread, 2 veg.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(608,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(608,5,'These recipes are from the back of "The Whole Story" a publication of the Whole Foods Market... (March/April Issue)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(608,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(608,7,'Shared by Linda Martin');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(609,1,'Mix water*, salt (reduce if you want), coriander & garlic in a bowl.  Dip tempeh chunks into bowl & then coat with cornstarch.  Deep fry in hot oil till golden brown.  Drain on paper towels & set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(609,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(609,3,'SAUCE: Heat oil in skillet & saute onion for 4 to 5 minutes.  Add water, honey, soy sauce, vinegar, tahini, ginger & green onion.  Bring to a boil. Dissolve cornstarch in 2 tb water & stir into sauce.  Stir till thickened. Place tempeh chunks into the sauce & cook briefly over low heat till heated through.  Serve over rice or pasta.  Great hot or cold.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(609,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(609,5,'* I usually save the mixture that I''ve used to dip the tempeh chunks & add enough water to make up to 1/2 cup.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(609,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(609,7,'Adapted from Frances Moore Lappe, "Diet for a Small Planet".');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(610,1,'Bring water to a boil & cook lentils for 25 minutes.  Drain & set aside. combine vinegar, honey, tamari, ginger & water.  Bring to a boil.  mix cornstarch with a little water & add to sauce.  Saute onion in oil till soft.  Add pieces of celery & cook for 5 minutes over medium heat.  Add lentils, mix well.  Add sauce, simmer 5 minutes.  Serve over rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(610,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(610,3,'"Vegetarian Times Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(611,1,'In heavy stainless steel or enamelled skillet saute cabbage and garlic 3 to 4 minutes, stirring to coat well with oil.  Add remaining ingredients. Combine well.  Bake in preheated 350 degrees oven 40 to 60 minutes or until tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(611,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(611,3,'Source Unknown');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(612,1,'Serve these sweet-and-sour nibbles as cocktail food or give jars of them to friends.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(612,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(612,3,'Cook carrots in boiling water until crisp-tender. Drain. Cut carrots into 3-inch-long sticks and pack upright in small hot sterilized jars. Combine sugar, vinegar, water and salt in saucepan. Tie cinnamon stick and pickling spice in cheesecloth bag and add to vinegar mixture. Boil 5 to 8 minutes. Fill jars with boiling syrup, leaving 1/2-inch head space. Adjust lids and process in boiling water bath 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(612,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(612,5,'(C) 1992 The Los Angeles Times');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(612,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(612,7,'Posted by Karen Mintzias in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,1,'Prepare pie crust & set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,3,'Pre heat oven to 375F.  Wash & scrub potatoes. Place in a baking pan, brush  skins with some olive oil & bake for 1 1/2 hours till very soft. Cool & then peel.  Mash & add the rest of the ingredients.  Blend till the mixture has a creamy consistency.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,5,'Reduce oven to 350F.  Spoon mixture into pie crust.  Garnish with walnuts. Bake for 1 hour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,7,'Chill or cool to room temperature before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,9,'Variation.  Add 1 to 2 cups cooked chick peas to the sweet potato before cooking the pie.  Ensure they rae well mashed.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(613,11,'"Vegetarian Times" October, 1991');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(614,1,'Put all vegetables with the bay leaf in a soup pot.  Add water & bring to a boil.  Simmer for about one hour.  Stir occasionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(614,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(614,3,'Just befroe serving, add lemon juice & paprika.  Remove bay leaf.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(614,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(614,5,'Joel Rapp, "Mother Earth''s Vegetarian Feasts"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,1,'Heat oil in a large casserole.  Saute onion & garlic until the onion is tender.  Add cumin & coriander.  Saute for another minute over medium heat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,3,'Add cayenne pepper, lentils, bay leaf & water.  Bring to a boil.  Add salt & pepper to taste, cover, reduce heat & simmer for 45 minutes.  Simmer only until the lentils are just tender.  Adjust seasonings.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,5,'Just before serving, bring back to a simmer & add the noodles.  Cook until al dente, about 4 to 10 minutes.  Serve at once in bowls.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,7,'In place of vermicelli, use wholewheat spaghetti noodles or macaroni.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(615,9,'Martha Rose Shulman, "Spicy Vegetarian Feasts"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,1,'Place burghul in a bowl and cover with the cold water.  Leave to soak for 30 minutes.  Drain through a fine sieve, pressing with back of a spoon to extract moisture.  Spread onto a cloth and leave to dry further.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,3,'Meanwhile, prepare parsley.  Wash well, shake off excess moisture and remove thick stalks.  Wrap in a tea towel and place in refrigerator to crisp and dry.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,5,'Put burghul into a mixing bowl and add spring onions.  Squeeze mixture with hand so that burghul absorbs onion flavour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,7,'Chop parsley fairly coarsley, measure and add to burghul with mint.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,9,'Beat olive oil with lemon juice and stir in salt and pepper.  Add to salad and toss well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,11,'Peel and seed tomatoes and cut into dice.  Gently stir into salad.  Cover and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,13,'Serve in salad bowl lined with crisp lettuce leaves.  Lemon juice and salt mixture is served in a jug so that it may be added according to individual taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,15,'Serves 6-8');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,16,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(616,17,'Source: The Complete Middle East Cookbook, by Tess Mallos Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,1,'In a small bowl place the olive oil, lemon juice, salt and pepper.  Whisk the ingredients together.  Set the dressing aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,3,'Place the bulgur in a strainer and rinse it with cold water.  Squeeze out the excess water.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,5,'In a medium bowl place the bulgur, parsley, mint, garlic, tomatoes, scallions, onions, and green bell peppers.  Toss the ingredients together well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,7,'Add the dressing and toss it in well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,9,'On each individual serving plate, arrange the romaine lettuce.  Place the bulgur salad on top.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(617,11,'Source: Papa Garo''s - Redondo Beach, California "Southern California Beach Recipe" by Joan and Carl Stromquist ISBN: 0-9622807-3-9 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(618,1,'Process the above in a blender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(618,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(618,3,'From: ded@kps.se (David Edwards /DP)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,1,'Place beans in a bowl and cover well with cold water.  Leave to soak for 2 days, changing water 2 or 3 times.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,3,'Drain beans and remove skins by pressing each firmly with fingers.  Bean should pop out, otherwise tear skin with fingernail then squeeze.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,5,'Pass cleaned beans through food grinder using fine screen.  Combine with spring onion, parsley, coriander, garlic, salt, peppers and soda.  Pass through grinder twice more, then knead to a paste.  Let mixture rest for 30 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,7,'With wet hands shape about a tablespoon of mixture at a time into thick patties about 4 cm (1-1/2 inches) in diameter.  Dip each side in sesame seeds if desired.  Place on a tray and leave at room temperature for 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,9,'Heat oil to 180øC (350øF) or until a cube of bread turns golden in 1 minute.  Fry tameya a few at a time until deep golden brown, turning to brown evenly.  Each lot should take 5 minutes to cook.  Drain on paper towels.  Serve hot with flat bread such as Khoubiz, Salata Tahina and assorted salad vegetables, such as tomato, cucumber, sweet peppers and lettuce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,11,'Food processor method: Combine prepared ingredients and process in 2 lots using steel blade.  Mix well to evenly distribute flavours, rest mixture 30 minute then fry as directed above.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,13,'Makes 30');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(619,15,'Source: The Complete Middle East Cookbook by Tess Mallos Typos by: Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(620,1,'Heat a wok or large frying-pan over high heat and add the oil.  Put in the preserved vegetables, garlic, and ginger and stir-fry for 1 minute.  Add the rice wine, chili bean sauce, sesame paste, soy sauce, sugar, and stock.  Reduce the heat and simmer for 3 minutes over low heat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(620,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(620,3,'Bring a large pot of water to boil and cook the noodles for 2 minutes if they are fresh and 5 minutes if dried.  Drain well in a colander.  Divide the noodles into individual bowls and ladle the sauce over them.  Serve at once.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(620,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(620,5,'Source: Asian Vegetarian Feast - by Ken Hom William Morrow and Company, Inc. - New York ISBN: 0-688-07753-6 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(621,1,'Gently press tofu to remove exces moisture.  Slice into large pieces & then cut each chunk crosswise.  Set aside.  Place green onions & ginger in a food processor & process briefly.  With the machine running, drop in garlic cloves, one at a time.  Process 30 seconds.  Add remaining ingredients.  Process 1 minute.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(621,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(621,3,'BROCHETTES: Place onions, mushroom, tofu & marinade in a glass dish & seal.  Refrigerate overnight.  Prepare grill next day.  Quarter onions & remove papery outer skins.  Skewer vegetables & tofu alternately.  Place on hot grill & brush with remaining marinade.  Cover grill tightly & allow to smoke for 5 minutes.  Don''t peek.  Trun once & cook for another 3 to 5 minutes.  Garnish with cilantro & lemon wedges.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(621,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(621,5,'PER SERVING: 322 Cal.; 21g Prot.; 9g Fat; 36g Carb.; 1mg Chol.; 514mg Sod.; 5g Fiber.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(621,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(621,7,'"Vegetarian Times" July, 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(622,1,'Heat a pot of salted water & boil the noodles till tender.  Rinse, drain & keep warm on a serving dish.  Heat oil in a wok & stir fry onion, broccoli, mushrooms, water chestnuts & bamboo shoots for 2 minutes.  Add bean sprouts & fry for 1 minute.  Place on dish with noodles.  Keep warm.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(622,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(622,3,'Add a little more oil & fry ginger & garlic for 1 minute.  Stir in salt, sugar, soy sauce, sherry & sesame oil.  Add bean curd.  Fry gently till bean curd begins to brown.  Mix together with the noodles & vegetables. Keep warm.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(622,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(622,5,'Add a little more oil to the wok & fry the sesame seeds, nuts, green onion & pepper till the nuts begin to brown.  Use a granish for the rest of the meal.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(622,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(622,7,'Jack Santa Maria, "Chinese Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(623,1,'Mix together the dry ingredients.  Cut in the shortening.  Add water, a little at a time & mix thoroughly.  Using more flour if necessary, knead dough lightly until it is well mixed & not sticky.  Roll dough with rolling pin to 1/2" thickness & cut with a cookie cutter.  Place on cookie sheet & bake at 400F for 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(623,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(623,3,'Variation, add 1/2 c currants before adding the water.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(623,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(623,5,'Makes 18 biscuits.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(623,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(623,7,'Posted by Mark Satterly in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(624,1,'Heat 1 tb oil in a large skillet & saute tempeh, onion, bulgur & mushrooms for 3 to 4 minutes.  Add water & soy sauce.  Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat & simmer 15 minutes.  Let cool to room temperature.  Combine with remaining ingredients & mix well.  Chill for at least 2 hours before serving.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(624,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(624,3,'Frances Moore Lappe, "Diet for a Small Planet"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(625,1,'Steam tempeh for 20 minutes.  Allow to cool enough to handle.  Cut into cubes slightly smaller than 1/2 inch.  Combine with remaining ingredients & mix lightly.  Serve on a bed of lettuce or as a sandwich filling.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(625,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(625,3,'* I use tofu based mayonnaise, blend the tofu well with a touch of salt & pepper, lemon juice & a crushed garlic clove.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(625,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(625,5,'Frances Moore Lappe, "Diet for a Small Planet"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(626,1,'Pre-heat oven to 300F.  Heat oil in large skillet.  Saute onions & paprika till golden.  Add 1 1/2 cups stock & miso.  Bring to a boil.  Add tempeh, reduce heat & simmer 35 to 40 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(626,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(626,3,'Blend soy sauce, vinegar & tahini with remaining stock.  Add to the skillet, stirring as it thickens. Be careful not to let it boil.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(626,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(626,5,'Garnish with scallions.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(626,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(626,7,'"Vegetarian Times" November, 1991');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(627,1,'* Follow instructions on your tempeh to make it ready to eat; the tempeh I make is already pre-cooked and it is made with soybeans and barley.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(627,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(627,3,'Directions: Add all ingredients except the last two to a food processor and process until smooth. Then add the last two, mix by hand and then form into ball.  Chill for at least two hours.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(627,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(627,5,'Serve with veggies or crackers.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(627,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(627,7,'Comments and/or improvements are welcome. Gunter Pfaff, 73740,2515');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,1,'Saute onion briefly in oil in a large, heavy, oven-prof 4 quart pot. Ad garlic if desiredl Add chopped tomaoto and tomato puree. Add sauerkraut. Stir, cover then simmer on low heat 5-10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,3,'Cut the cap off the vell peppers. Scoop out the insides, and discard the seeds.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,5,'In a mixing bowl, combine filling ingredients including tempeh, miso, bread crumbs, cooked beans, and seasonings. Mix with your hands briefly to distribute herbs and spices evenly. Diide filling into 4 balls, then stuff into each of the bell peppers.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,7,'Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Place bell peppers, upright, in the pot with the sauce. Cover and let simmer on top of the stove for 10 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,9,'Transfer the pot to the oven. Bake for 30 minutes. Remove lid and bake another 20-15 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,11,'Serve piping hot in bowls, topped with sauce. Accompany with whole grain bread or tortillas and salad.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,13,'Variation: in place of fresh tomato and tomato puree, use 2 cups finely grated carrot or minced winter squash, then add 1 cup of water or soup stock.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(628,15,'Per serving: 352 cal, 12 g fat From _Vegetarian Journal_, Vegetarian Resource Group, May-June 1993 DEEANNE                      at 14:52 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(629,1,'Place all ingredients, except corn, into a pot.  Whisk togetehr & bring to a boil, stirring constantly.  Reduce heat & simmer for 1 minute.  Remove from heat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(629,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(629,3,'Prepare grill.  Husk corn & grill covered for 5 to 10 minutes. When almost done, baste with glaze two or three times.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(629,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(629,5,'PER SERVING: 70 Cal.; 1g Prot.; 0.4g Fat; 15g Carb.; 6mg Sod.; 4g Fiber.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(629,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(629,7,'"Vegetarian Times" July, 1993');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,1,'To make marinade, combine tamari, mirin, pineapple juice, ginger, garlic and red pepper flakes in a shallow baking dish.  Place tempeh burgers in marinade and set aside 15 minutes.  Turn burgers occasionally to coat with marinade.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,3,'Combine pineapple, red onion, green pepper, tomato, garlic, jalapeno, cilantro and spices in a small bowl.  Refrigerate until serving time.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,5,'Remove tempeh burgers from marinade and grill over medium-hot coals 5 minutes each side.  Serve immediately with Pineapple Salsa.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,7,'PER SERVING: Calories: 213           Grams of fat: 6.4 Cholesterol: 0          % Fat Calories: 27 Grams Fiber: 6.6');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(630,9,'Source: Delicious! Magazine, July/August 1993 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(631,1,'     Mince garlic.  Remove seeds and dice bell pepper.  In dutch oven, cook onion, garlic and raw rice in oil until onion is tender and rice is lightly browned.  Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.  Stir in cumin and black pepper.  Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.  Remove from heat. Stir in bell pepper.  Let stand covered until all liquid is absorbed, about 5 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(631,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(631,3,'Posted by Sandee Eveland in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,1,'*Note: The book says to peel the cucumbers only if they are waxed and even then leave on a few strips.  I say to remove all the peel if it''s been waxed.  Yuck.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,3,'In a bowl, generously salt the sliced cucumbers.  Allow to sit for at least 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,5,'Combine the other ingredients.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,7,'Squeeze out as much of the cucumber juice as you can, by wringing a handful at a time in a double layer of cheesecloth or a dish towel.  Twist until you can extract no more juice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,9,'Combine the squeezed cucumbers and the sauce in a serving bowl and refrigerate until ready to serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(632,11,'Source: Sundays at Moosewood Restaurant Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,1,'This is a superb substitute for the traditional Thanksgiving turkey.  It''s also good for other times of the year!  It''s really the dressing that carries this dish.  The corn oil gives it that wonderful buttery taste that poultry dressing usually has.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,3,'DIRECTIONS ========== Wash the tofu, pat it dry, and cut it into small pieces.  Put the tofu, arrowroot, soup base, salt, pepper, and agar flakes in a food processor and blend to a smooth paste.  Oil and flour the loaf pan (or line it with baking liner paper after oiling).  Spread a layer of tofu paste inside the pan, lining the bottom and all four sides.  (Spread only a thin layer on the ends.)  Use all but about 1 cup of the paste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,5,'Firmly but gently press the dressing into the pan, on top of the tofu paste "liner".  Try to avoid displacing the tofu.  Cover the dressing with the remaining tofu, carefully sealing the edges.  Cover the pan with foil, making certain the foil doesn''t come in contact with the tofu.  (The tofu will eat into the foil.)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,7,'Bake in a preheated oven at 350 F for 30 to 40 minutes.  Then remove the foil cover, glaze the top of the loaf with the dissolved barley malt syrup, turn the oven up to 450 F, and continue baking for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and allow the loaf to cool for about 10 minutes.  Unmold, slice, and serve hot with a sauce of your choice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,9,'SAGE DRESSING:  Saute onions, celery, carrots, and garlic in oil for 5 minutes.  Add the sage, basil, soup base, salt and pepper, and continue cooking 5 minutes longer.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,11,'Add the water and bring to a simmer.  Stir in the bread crumbs and cook for a few minutes.  Then remove from heat.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(633,13,'Source: Friendly Foods - by Brother Ron Pickarski, O.F.M. ISBN: 0-89815-377-8 Typed by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(634,1,'Drain & wash chick peas.  Cook for 50 to 60 minutes, or until tender.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(634,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(634,3,'Meanwhile, cook the macaroni in a large pan of boiling water, lightly salted for 10 minutes, or until just resistant to the bite.  Drain.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(634,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(634,5,'Saute garlic in a large skillet in olive oil for a few minutes.  Add cooked, drained chick peas & macaroni.  Mix in the basil & parsley.  Cook over a very low heat, stirring occasionally, til the flavours are absorbed & the mixture is heated through.  Season with salt & pepper & serve hot with a crisp green salad.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(634,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(634,7,'Adapted from Sarah Brown''s "Vegetarian Kitchen"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,1,'Preheat oven to 375F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,3,'Heat oil in a skillet & fry the buckwheat for 2 to 3 minutes.  Add onions & mushrooms & cook for a few more minutes.  Pour in the wine & stock & bring to a boil.  Reduce heat & simmer for 20 minutes.  Add more stock if necessary.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,5,'Grind the walnuts finely.  Wash & cook spinach without water for 6 minutes.  Drain off any excess liquid & chop thoroughly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,7,'When buckwheat is cooked, remove pan from heat & let cool slightly.  Stir in walnuts & spinach.  Mix in the herbs & mix well.  Season to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,9,'Grease a 1 LB loaf tin & press in the mixture.  Bake for 50 to 60 minutes till the top is dark brown & feels firm to the touch.  Let it stand for 10 minutes, then turn out onto a plate.  Serve with roasted vegetables & greens.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(635,11,'Sarah Brown, "Vegetarian Kitchen"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,1,'Place the pieces of tofu in a large, shallow dish.  Mix together the wine, tamari, and garlic.  Pour the mixture over the tofu, add water as need to cover it, and let it marinate for at least one hour.  If the tofu is going to marinate for more than an hour, place in the refrigerator.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,3,'Place the marinated tofu on a well-oiled cookie sheet, reserving the marinade.  Bake at 375oF for 35-45 minutes or until crispy and brown. Turn the tofu over once during the baking so that it browns on both sides.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,5,'While the tofu bakes, heat the oil in a large pan and slowly saute the onions.  When the onions are almost tender, add the mushrooms and the herbs.  Saute for a few minutes more.  Add the flour and mix well. Remove the pan from the heat and stir in a little of the marinade. Continue stirring until a paste is formed.  Return the pan to the heat and slowly add the remaining marinade, stirring constantly.  Add the baked tofu and simmer until thickened.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,7,'Serve over pasta, rice or millet.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(636,9,'From: allison@Ingres.COM (ALLISON FINK, HR EXT 2907)');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(637,1,'Mash tofu.  Combine with carrot, leeks & sesame seeds.  Knead as if kneading bread, for 3 minutes.  When dough is smooth, moisten palms with oil & shape into patties.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(637,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(637,3,'Fry patties in oil as if frying regular meat hamburger.  Fry till crisp & nicely browned, about 4 minutes per side.  Drain & serve hot in a hamburger bun with mustard, lettuce, ketchup, pickle & tomato.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(637,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(637,5,'Frances Moore Lappe, "Diet for a Small Planet"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(638,1,'Mash the tofu. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(638,2,' Chill and serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(638,3,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(638,4,'DEEANNE                      at 14:52 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(639,1,'Place all ingredients in blender and blend until creamy. Serve on bread or baked potatoes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(639,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(639,3,'DEEANNE                      at 14:52 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(640,1,'Blend all ingredients in a food processor until very smooth.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(640,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(640,3,'This delicious and healthful combination will compliment your garden beauties while it woos the most timid tofu skeptic.  You cna serve it with fresh vegetables or crackers or use it as a sandwich filling.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(640,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(640,5,'Makes about 2 cups.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(640,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(640,7,'Source: Cooking from the Garden - by Rosalind Creasy ISBN: 0-87156--731-8 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,1,'In a small bowl, stir together peanut butter, soy sauce, water, sesame oil, ginger, vinegar, and sugar until smooth.  Mix in garlic, sesame seed, and onions.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,3,'Spoon about 1/4 of the peanut butter mixture into an 8-inch-square pan. Cut tofu ito 4 equal slices.  Lay slices side by side in pan (trim slices to fit, if needed, tucking scraps into corners).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,5,'Spoon remaining sauce over tofu.  If made ahead, cover and chill up to 4 hours.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,7,'Bake, uncovered, in a 375 F oven until tofu is hot in center, about 25 minutes.  Transfer tofu to plates with a spatula; spoon sauce onto tofu and rice.  Offer chutney to add to taste.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,9,'Per serving: 228 cal.; 15 g protein; 15 g fat (2.4 g sat.); 11 g carbo.; 1,115 mg sodium; 0 mg chol.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(641,11,'Source: Amelia Lane - Bend, Oregon Sunset magazine - April, 1992 Typed for you by Karen Mintzias');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(642,1,'To drain tofu, line a plate with paper towels, placew tofu on top of plate & cover with more towels.  Press with a good weight fpr 10 minutes.  Then cut into 2" cubes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(642,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(642,3,'place cubes in a bowl with garlic, onion, oregano & tamari sauce & vinegar.  Let marinate, stirring frequently for 30 minutes or more.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(642,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(642,5,'Pre-heat broiler or grill.  Skewer vegetables, adding tofu cubes alternately.  Broil or grill till lightly browned & heated through.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(642,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(642,7,'"Vegetarian Times" September, 1990');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(643,1,'Heat oil in a skillet, add garlic, onion, pepper, carrot & celery.  Season with 1 tb tamari.  Cook till vegetables are tender.  Remove from heat & put in a large mixing bowl.  Add mashed tofu.  Cut bread into crouton sized pieces & quick fry in remaining oil with rest of tamari, garlic powder & 5 tb nutritional yeast.  Add to tofu mixture.  Add rest of the ingredients.  Mix well.  Place in a well oiled casserole dish & press down very well.  Bake at 350F for 35 minutes.  Allow to cool slightly, then turn out on a plate.  Slice & serve.  Excellent cold too.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(643,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(643,3,'"The Cookbook for People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(644,1,'Combine all ingredients in a blender and beat until smooth and creamy.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(644,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(644,3,'DEEANNE                      at 14:52 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(645,1,'Combine all ingredients in blender and puree until smooth. Use the lesser amount of water for a light cream consistency, the full amount for milk.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(645,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(645,3,'Makes about 1 cup.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(645,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(645,5,'DEEANNE                      at 02:51 EDT');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(646,1,'Mix the water and egg replacer together.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(646,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(646,3,'Blend the remaining ingredients, except for the tofu, in a food processor. Process until well mixed, then stir in the tofu.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(646,4,'');
