INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(677,3,'Drain the beancurd sheets and spread out on a flat surface.  Place a line of the cooled filling along one edge of each sheet and roll to form a long sausage.  Place the 3 sausages in a steamer and steam for 15 minutes. Remove and leave to cool.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(677,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(677,5,'When ready to serve, deep-fry the sausages until golden brown, drain and slice into 1/4-inch (6 mm) rounds and serve on a bed of lettuce and mint leaves with Plum Sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(677,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(677,7,'Vatcharin Bhumichitr "Thai Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(678,1,'Heat oil in the wok & add the garlic & walnuts.  Fry stirring frequently till the nuts are slightly browned.  Remove them with a slotted spoon. Add the prepared vegetables & cook till slightly softened.  Stir in the rice & season to taste.  Pour in the stock & bring to a boil.  Cover, reduce heat & simmer gently for 10 minutes or so.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(678,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(678,3,'Mix together the tomatoes & olives.  Stir corn & peas into the vegetable mixture in the wok.  Place tomatoes & olives on top, do not stir them in & replace the lid.  Simmer for 5 minutes.  All the stock should be absorbed. Before serving, stir in olives & tomatoes, nuts & herbs.  Serve with a salad.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(678,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(678,5,'Bridget Jones, "Wok Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(679,1,'Into a pot of boiling water, drop the cauliflower, carrots, bell pepper, and green peas and blanch for 3 to 5 minutes.  Drain the vegetables and plunge them into a bowl of ice water to stop cooking. Set aside.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(679,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(679,3,'Grind the almonds, cashews, and onions with water to create a smooth paste. In a pan, heat the oil until smoking, add the nut paste and stir-fry for 2 to 3 minutes.  Add the pepper and chili powder, then the blanched vegetables.  Add the potatoes, tomatoes, and paneer (homemade cheese). Continue stirring while heating through. Add mint and salt. Makes 4 to 6 servings.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(679,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(679,5,'From: The Shiva Indian Restaurant, 2514 Times Blvd, Houston Texas');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,1,'Heat oil in a skillet   Add the garlic & onions & saute for 3 minutes. Add the carrots, celery, green peppers & mushrooms & continue to saute for 5 minutes. Season well with the herbs & spices, including the tamari.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,3,'Combine the mashed potatoes with the soy milk.  Add the saute to the potato mixture.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,5,'In a bowl, combine the oil, orange juice & salt.  Gradually add the flour til lthe texture is moist & pliable.  Roll the dough out on a floured board.  Place rolled dough in a rectangular casserole so that the edges flop over the sides.  Spoon the vegetables into the centre of the dough. moisten the edges of the dough & seal into a loaf shape.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,7,'Place on a cookie shhet or leave in the casserole, making sure that whatever you use is oiled to prevent sticking.  Bake for 40 minutes at 375F.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,9,'Serve with vegetables on the side, such as mashed turnip, peas or beans, & cabbage.  Or whatever.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(680,11,'"The Cookbook For People Who Love Animals"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(681,1,'Drain peas & rinse well.  Place in medium pot with water & 1/2 cup of chopped onion.  Stir in garlic, cumin, ginger, cayenne & salt.  Bring to a boil & simmer for 30 minutes, till all the liquid is absorbed.  Cool slightly.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(681,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(681,3,'In a blender, combine the peas with the remaining onions, pepper & cilantro.  Puree for 1 minute.  Transfer to a mixing bowl & add lemon juice & bread crumbs.  Mix well.  If too dry, add a little water.  Shape into 8 patties.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(681,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(681,5,'Heat 2 tb oil in a medium skillet.  Cook the patties for 7 minutes on each side.  Drain on paper towels.  Serve with peanut sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(681,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(681,7,'"Vegetarian Times", April 1992');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(682,1,'Place tortillas in shallow pan.  Spread salsa over them to soften them. Let sit for 5 minutes.  Turn tortiallas over & coat the other side.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(682,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(682,3,'While the tortillas are softening, heat oil in a skillet & saute onion for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.  Add garlic, eggplant, zucchini & sherry if using.  Cook, stirring often, for 5 minutes or so, till eggplant begins to stick.  Remove from heat & stir in chilies.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(682,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(682,5,'Pre-heat oven to 400F.  Lightly oil a baking tin.  Remove each tortilla from the sauce & fill with one quarter of the sauteed vegetables.  Roll up tortillas & place seam side down in baking tin.  Top with the rest of the sauce & cilantro.  Bake for 15 minutes, until evenly browned.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(682,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(682,7,'"Vegetarian Times" September, 1991');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,1,'Heat ghee in large skillet & fry the garlic & spices for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,3,'Blanch eggplants in boiling water for 4 to 5 minutes.  Drain & dice them.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,5,'Add all the vegetables, including the chili, to the pan.  Fry gently for 7 minutes, stirring to mix thoroughly.  Dissolve grated coconut in the boiling water & mix with vegetables.  Add tomatoes, cover & cook for 20 minutes.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,7,'Just before serving, stir in toasted cashews & serve over rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(683,9,'Sarah Brown''s "Vegetarian Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(684,1,'1. Saute onion and celery in oil in a large Dutch oven until soft.~ 2. Stir in flour; cook several minutes, stirring over medium heat.~ 3. Reduce heat; slowly add soy bean stock, stirring constantly.~ 4. Add carrots, potato, mushrooms, chopped tomato, herbs and seasonings; bring to boil to thicken, stirring constantly.~ 5. Remove from heat and set aside.~ 6. Alternate layers of soy beans and noodles in a greased 12x8x2-inch baking dish; pour some of the vegetable gravy over each layer. (Gravy should come almost to top of mixture.)~ 7. Arrange tomato slices over top; sprinkle with parsley.~ 8. Bake in preheated 350''F. oven 40 minutes.~');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(684,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(684,3,'Posted by Kaz Gover in Intercook');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(685,1,'Cut peeled & washed vegetables into small cubes.  Combine oil & 1 1/2 cups of vegetables.  Cook till ight brown.  Add flour & mix well.  Add a pint of water & the rest of the vegetables.  Cook slowly for about 90 minutes. Season to taste & serve with the dumplings.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(685,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(685,3,'DUMPLINGS: Work oil into flour, crumbs & nuts.  Add enough water to make a stiff dough.  Roll & cut into walnut sized pieces.  Cook for 25 minutes in rapidly boiling water.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(685,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(685,5,'"The Vegetarian Times Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(686,1,'Peel & coarsely chop the tomatoes & onions.  Coarsely chop the zucchini & peppers.  Combine in a bowl.  Process in a food processor in several batches till they are finely chopped.  Place in a large bowl, sprinkle with salt & let stand, covered, overnight.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(686,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(686,3,'Place vegetables in colander & drain excess liquid.  Place in a large pot, add vinegar & sugar & stir over low heat till the sugar is dissolved. Bring to a boil & simmer for 3 minutes.  Combine the remaining ingredients & blend till smooth.  Add to the vegetables & bring to a boil, stirring constantly.  Simmer till thickened.  Remove from heat & pour into warm sterile jars.  Seal.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(686,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(686,5,'Letts, "Jams, Pickles & Chutneys"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,1,'Soak the split peas in hot water for 1 hour & drain.  Wash the Mung beans well & pick out any loose stones & sticks, etc.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,3,'Combine rice, legumes, ghee, turmeric, asafetida, chili, ginger root, vegetables & stock in large pot.  Cook for about one hour.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,5,'Blend the vegetables at high speed to make a very creamy & smooth soup & return to the pot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,7,'Sprinkle in the ground coriander, cumin & garam masala.  Heat till almost boiling & simmer gently for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring to prevent burning.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,9,'Add the black pepper, salt & minced coriander & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(687,11,'Yamuna Devi, "The Art of Indian Vegetarian Cooking"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(688,1,'Heat oil in a soup pot & stir fry onion for 1 minute.  Add vegetables, salt, pepper & soy sauce.  Fry together for 2 minutes.  Add water & bring to a boil. Simmer till the vegetables are tender.  Add watercress & serve.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(688,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(688,3,'Jack Santa Maria, "Chinese Vegetarian Cookery"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(689,1,'Melt ghee in a wok or skillet.  Add ginger, garlic & onion & stir fry for 1 minute.  Add garam masala, chili powder, pepper, salt & soy sauce. Stir-fry for 30 seconds.  Add vegetables & mix well.  Remove from heat & place in a bowl.  Add tofu & toss well.  Allow to cool & drain off excess liquid.  Put 1 tb of filling into each momo wrapper & seal closed with a little water.  Steam over a steaming rack for 15 to 20 minutes.  Serve hot with momo sauce.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(689,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(689,3,'Adapted from Betty Jung, "The Kopan Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(690,1,'Melt ghee & stir-fry ginger, garlic & onion for 1 minute.  Add flour & continue to stir fry for fro 3 to 5 minutes, till golden in colour.  Add water a little at a time, whisking constantly to keep it smooth.  Add vegetables, tomatoes, tofu, green onions & bring to a boil.  Add the remaining ingredients.  Simmer for 10 minutes.  Thin with extra water if too thick.  Serve hot.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(690,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(690,3,'Adapted from Betty Jung, "The Kopan Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(691,1,'Heat ghee in a large pot.  Add cumin, coriander, ginger, garlic & onion & stir-fry for 1 minute.  Add turmeric, garam masala, chili powder, minced red chili & bay leaves.  Mix well & stir-fry for another minute.  Add vegetables, potatoes & tomatoes.  Mix well & cook for another 5 minutes. Add water & bring to a boil.  Add remaining ingredients.  Serve hot over boiled rice.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(691,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(691,3,'Adapted from Betty Jung, "The Kopan Cookbook"');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,1,'Put bulgar in a bowl of hot water, soak for 10 minutes or until tender,drain.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,3,'Heat oil in a skilled, saute mushrooms, carrots, onions, garlic for 15 mins. Let cook.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,5,'Grind walnuts and sunflower seeds, put into a bowl, add sesame seeds, bulgur, and wheat germ.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,7,'Mix sauteed vegetables with parsley, dill, cahini, chickpeas, tamari, lemon juice, cayenne, salt, pepper, and cumin until blended (small lumps ok).');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,8,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,9,'Add to the sesame-bulgur mixture, mix well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,10,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,11,'Chill thoroughly to firm the mixture.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,12,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,13,'Shape into patties, pat with oil, cook 4 minutes on each side, flip carefully with a Wide spatula to keep from falling apart.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,14,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,15,'Serve on toasted rolls with slices of tomato, sprouts, cucumber, yogurt.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,16,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,17,'Serves 8 to 10, depending upon size of patties/rolls.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,18,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,19,'Yum, with a nice chopped (medium dice) marinated fresh vegetable salad or coleslaw or carrot slaw.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,20,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(692,21,'From: swelch@pioneer.arc.nasa.gov (Shaun Welch) @Newsgroups: rec.food.recipes');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(693,1,'Mash up the tofu in a bowl and add salt, nutritional yeast, spices, tomato paste.  Chop the celery, caulflower, and onion finely and saute in oil.  When mostly cooked add the mushrooms, sliced.  When the mushrooms are done, add the vegetables to the tofu and mix well.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(693,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(693,3,'Cook the lasagne noodles in water until done.  This can be done beforehand to save time.  Grease your casserole pan lightly with some oil to help prevent sticking.  Place a layer of noodles down and spoon some tomato sauce over it.  Put a layer of tofu/veggies down.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(693,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(693,5,'Saute the chard (or spinach) in a pan with just a little bit of oil. When completely cooked down and soft, add half to the lasagne, spreading evenly over the layer.  Add more sauce then noodles, then tofu than another layer of chard.  Top with more sauce, more noodles and a large amount of sauce (to prevent any burning or drying out of the noodles when they''re cooked).  Preheat oven to about 350 or 375 and cook roughly 35 minutes, or until bubbly and hot.  SERVE!  I guarantee it''ll be among the best lasagne you''ve ever had....');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(693,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(693,7,'From: tara@starburst.umd.edu (Tara McDermott) @Newsgroups: rec.food.veg');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(694,1,'~- Combine all ingredients except rice papers and oil.  Cut the rice papers into quarters.  Wet the surface of each paper with water (use your fingers or a brush) and within about 1 min the paper will become flexible enough to be filled.  Place about 1 tbsp of the filling on each paper and roll.  Heat the oil in a wok to about 350 deg. F.  Place rolls, flaps-down, into oil and cook 20 min (10 min each side), until completely done.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(694,2,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(694,3,' Serve with Buddhist Nuoc Leo.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(694,4,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(694,5,'~- Disclaimer: This recipe is fat-city.  There is another form of spring roll skin which is inherently sticky and stretchy (white and barely opaque), and doesn''t require deep frying. (One could lighly saute the carrots and potatoes beforehand.) I can''t remember what this wrapper is called.  BTW - With this alternate type of "spring roll" fresh chinese parsley or cilantro is often included.');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(694,6,'');
INSERT INTO instruction VALUES(694,7,'~- Side note: About forming a spring roll from quartered rice paper...');
